        <Race id="1469" parentID="1462" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="2" createDate="2011-07-15T13:32:48" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:47" nodeName="Round 3 Malaysia" urlName="round-3-malaysia" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1462,1469" isDoc="">
          <race>7</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><strong>Flouncy</strong><br />One of my fav tracks. Lovely speedy go kart track. Nothing to tell, got pole, got away, Lambo was a few lengths back for a couple of laps, then he disappeared to be replaced by kikz. I had a comfy lead so just maintained pace, turned the engine down and drove to preserve tires. Eventually kikz disappeared so I just cruised around quickly and cleanly. Apart from a slight twitch on turn 1 lap 1 that I caught, a flawless drive.<br /><br /><strong>Atomic Lambo</strong><br />I would vote this and China as the most technical tracks in the calander. Sepang Has at least 3 or 4 very very technical corners that if you don't get right you lose lap time. Any how qualifying I went out early and banked a hot lap. It was solid but not fast, there was easly another 6 tenths or more to get from it. I went out on a second set of tires and was up 5 tenths in the first sector alone when I caught up to Mac dude which was unfortunate because I think that would have been a very hot lap. There was not enough time to pit and put another set on so I went out and tried on the same set. Unfortunately not as much grip as it had on the opening lap and only went up about 3 tenths on my time. Had to settle for 3rd on the grid, but easly could have been 2nd and might have troubled Ben for pole. The race I had a good start off the line. Went into the first corner right on the gearbox of Ben. Ben made a small mistake out of turn one and nearly lost it but did well to hold onto it. Going into turn 3 I breaked to turn in and Bollum comes flying out of nowhere taking me off the track. I resumed just behind Bollum and fast starting Fredz. Turn 4 fredz went off, and into turn 5 bollum took a strange line and I made a solid pass on him. I spent the next 3 odd laps catching up to Ben which I did. However on turn 9 turning into the corner, Kikz hit me and I lost the place. Not sure how you thought there was room to do that or if you out breaked yourself but it came from no where. I resumed in 3rd but had Ghost all over me. Going intot the final corner I got tagged but still ok, but on the next lap got tagged again and spun. However in a show of great sportsman ship Ghost waited till I resumed and allowed me to take my place, and in my opinion based on the finishing times, probably easily cost him victory. I made a mistake on the next lap that put ghost back infront of me anyway. I followed for another 2 laps and we both pitted on lap 8 or 9 with me right behind Ghost. Must have been a quick pitstop as I then came out ahead of him. But I struggled on the hard tires for a lap or two and eventually he passed me when I made a mistake. From then on it was a lonely race. Ghost obviously with that delay of 15 odd seconds letting me through and then the delay in the pits probably might have cost him. Overall a dissapointing result considering the early laps.<br /><br /><strong>TurrbalTerror</strong><br />Malaysia was interesting. I went faster in qualifying practice than I did in multiplayer mode. Not sure way. I wouldn't have got pole. I probably still would have been fourth with a mid 1:35, but I just couldn't do it. The first 5 or 6 laps were fantastic. I got off the line decentish and followed Ghost into the turn but he slowed rather drastically and I think someone tapped him. I took it pretty easy through the first few turns, so as not to trip up, and was 6th through those first. By the time I got the end of the lap I was a close 4th with Ghost right in front. I felt I had a lot more speed and was keeping up easily. Not sure what happened to ghost. I think he ran wide. Anyway, I took my opportunity and closed up behind Lambo and Flouncy not far ahead. I was glued to Lambo's gearbox on through turns 7 and 8. Coming in to T9 I took my chance and stuck my nose up the inside. Lambo turned in and I hit him. My fault. After that I took caught up behind Flouncy give or take a second or two. Pit stops came a few laps later and I pitted first I think. I came out in fourth again but got second back after the pitstops were done. Ghost started catching me pretty quickly at about lap 15 and I defended my line. Not sure when the pass was made or why, but Ghost took off after that and I settled for the bottom of the podium. My first this year.</p>]]></bodyText>
