        <Race id="1473" parentID="1462" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="6" createDate="2011-07-15T13:34:12" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:47" nodeName="Round 7 Turkey" urlName="round-7-turkey" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1462,1473" isDoc="">
          <race>11</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>The Season 3 atomicf1 Turkish GP was a close fought affair from the outset, and with the top qualifiers separated by less than a second the indicators were there early. </p>
<p>The first corner was not without incident, as pole sitter bobaj0r led from TurrbalTerror and fast starting Flouncy.  TurrbalTerror braked early, to leave Flouncy room and was nudged by Atomic Lambo enough to tap Flouncy who was trying to go round the outside.</p>
<p>It looked like being a hard fought battle between the Mclaren teammates until bobaj0r went off on the entry to turn 7, giving a clear lead to TurrbalTerror.  Krispy89 and Fredzfrog made brilliant starts through the first few turns but couldn't keep their cars planted on track after turn 4 of lap 1. </p>
<p>TurrbalTerror and Ghost pitted at the end of lap seven, giving the lead to Flouncy who led until lap 16, when the chasing pair of HolyGhost79 and TurrbalTerror caught, with TurrbalTerror effecting a pass through turns 2, 3, and 4, before Flouncy spun out of contention on the exit of turn 9.</p>
<p>From there, it a was a quiet race to the flag for TurrbalTerror and HolyGhost, with Flouncy finishing in a hard fought third.</p>
<p> </p>]]></bodyText>
