        <Race id="1474" parentID="1462" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="7" createDate="2011-07-15T13:34:46" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:48" nodeName="Round 8 Canada" urlName="round-8-canada" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1462,1474" isDoc="">
          <race>12</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Everyone was expecting it, an Atomic Lambo win, on this one of his more dominant tracks.  The event started well for Atomic Lambo, with pole position by a small margin over Flouncy. </p>
<p>Atomic Lambo held the usually fast starting Flouncy at bay with some aggressive defending through the turn 3, where arguably Flouncy had his wheels past the mid point of the Force India car. No doubt one for the stewards and the fans on internet forums around the world to argue over. Once Atomic Lambo was through there was little stand in his way, besides the concrete wall on the inside of the pit straight, which attract him, along with a number of other drivers throughout the race.<br /><br />After the round of scheduled stops the race had a new leader, HolyGhost79 who had pulled away to an impressive lead, followed by Flouncy, TurrbalTerror, and Atomic Lambo.  Atomic Lambo made his move when TurrbalTerror lost traction and ended facing perpendicular to the racing line, before a correcting - losing a few seconds.  <br /><br />Krispy89 had an impressive drive on his return to racing weekend, giving the more established drivers a hard time at moments before succumbing to his own inconsistency. Krispy89 is a driver to watch and with a little more consistency he will be a regular podium contender.  <br /><br />McLaren number two and recent returnee had a race he'll soon forget, with an unspiring qualifying and a drive backwards through the pack, his lack of track time evident.</p>]]></bodyText>
