        <Race id="1476" parentID="1462" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="9" createDate="2011-07-15T13:35:26" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:48" nodeName="Round 10 Britian" urlName="round-10-britian" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1462,1476" isDoc="">
          <race>14</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>It was clear from the off that Flouncy meant business at Silverstone.  His pole time of 1:31.085 stands as the fastest lap we've yet seen of this circuit at a race meet and was significantly faster than second placed HolyGhost79. This gird had a larger spread that the previous few races.</p>
<p>Race day threw up another doozie, with heavy rain yet again.  Flouncy made a clean start as the pack slipped and slid through the first few corners, battling over minor positions.  The end of lap 1 was exciting, as HolyGhost79, bobaj0r, and TurrbalTerror all jockeyed for 2nd position coming out of the last corner.  bobaj0r got squeezed by HolyGhost79 into TurrbalTerror as HolyGhost79 past TurrbalTerror, but both went off on turn 1 of lap 2 and bobaj0r was back in second place before his own mistakes cost him a higher finish.</p>
<p>TurrbalTerror lost more and more ground over the first five laps as he drove clean off the track on more corners than not, losing out a whooping gap of 45 seconds to bobaj0r in fourth place.  It was a gap that was to stay consistent until the end of the race.</p>
<p>Flouncy had his own misfortune when his steering dettached from the cockpit and he was lucky to salvage fourth place in front of a luckless Atomic Lambo who was forced to pull off track to take answer his phone.  Maybe Force India will invest in a handsfree before the next event. Although driving whilst talking on the phone is not against FIA regulations.</p>
<p>The misfortunes of two of the leading front runners was the fortunes of the fans, as it enabled the chasing pack to close up in points, but HolyGhost79 to extend his points lead ever so marginally.  Fortunately over the whole weekend, Flouncy and HolyGhost both had finished in P1 and P4, with only qualifying points difference the decider, and that swung in second place Flouncy's direction.</p>]]></bodyText>
