        <Race id="1466" parentID="1462" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="17" createDate="2011-07-15T13:28:46" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:50" nodeName="Round 18 Brazil" urlName="round-18-brazil" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1462,1466" isDoc="">
          <race>22</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Now the race is over one thing is clear, the championship battle is not.  Brazil shouldn’t have been surprising to anyone.  With HolyGhost79 dominating the previous race, history would have it that Brazil was Flouncy’s turn to dominate.  History, as it usually is, proved correct.  Flouncy tore up the Brazilian circuit colloquially known as the ‘Interlagos kart track’ in a record 1:09.985, putting pole position beyond the reach of his fellow drivers.  HolyGhost79 didn’t disappoint either, snatching 2nd position in the final stages of qualifying.  The front two rows of the grid were completed by the usual protagonists, Atomic Lambo and TurrbalTerror, making the most of his 10 laps of the Brazilian circuit in the last 2 seasons count.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Thankfully Brazil did not see a repeat of the first turn of Korea, with the entire pack getting away cleanly.  The top four blasted down the back straight for the first time, braking heavily for turn three on cold tyres.  MaverickROM wanted to make the most of his start and used TurrbalTerrors gearbox as his braking aid as he shot into fourth place.  TurrbalTerror recovered unfazed and in dead last and 10th place, in the one of the fullest fields ever to grace the competition.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>As the two contenders shot off into the distance, TurrbalTerror began his climb back through the pack and had claimed 9 by two turns later and was in 8th in another corner.  7th and 6th were dispatched on the same corners on lap two and scything through the pack was on in earnest and by the end of lap 4 he was in 5th place. </p>
<p>HolyGhost79 and Flouncy continued to trade sectors as they each attemped to assert supremacy over the other.  On lap 7 roxa3sora3 moved over onto the racing line to let TurrbalTerror by, which resulted, naturally, in a collision, as TurrbalTerror followed him onto the line.  The erractic Brisbanite continued on with only minor front wing damage; nothing a tweak to the front wing settings couldn’t fix.  Soon he was up in 3rd position, after passing MaverickROM and Atomic Lambo, the later having a short break in the infield at the bottom of the hill leading up the pit straight.  Turrball’s stint in 3rd was limited to only a couple of laps, as he misjudged just how far out into the track one of the barriers extend on the run up the hill toward the pits, and broke his front wing off entirely.  Fortunately it was a only a short distance to the pits. </p>
<p>With no hope of catching the leading duo, or that of Atomic Lambo, the oft erratic McLaren driver started, what ET Rom AU described as “playing” with the slower drivers, waiting for them to pass, only to repass them a number of corners later, then repeating.  While it’s not a new practice for TurrbalTerror, it’s most probably a practice that doesn’t sit well with race officials but none-the-less is hard to police. </p>
<p>When the flag dropped, it was the two that kept their noses clean, as they have most the season, that crossed the line in the places that mattered most.  This time with Flouncy in the lead and HolyGhost79 trailing.  What we’ve now got is a very exciting prospect.  The championship will be decided at the last race. </p>
<p>HolyGhost79 must bring his A game to walk away with the crown.  That much is certain.</p>]]></bodyText>
