        <Race id="1463" parentID="1462" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="18" createDate="2011-07-15T10:16:38" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:50" nodeName="Round 19 Abu Dhabi" urlName="round-19-abu-dhabi" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1462,1463" isDoc="">
          <race>23</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>In the end it came down to a little over 2 seconds.  That’s the size of the gap between champion Flouncy and contender HolyGhost79.  The fairytail didn’t go as planned though. Flouncy had eyes on a pole to flag win and he looked good at the midway point, with a lap of 1:40.259.  TurrbalTerror managed a 1:40.5, to provisionally fill second place.  A lap later TurrbalTerror crossed the line in 1:40.129, only to better it on the next lap with a 1:39.744.  Atomic Lambo and HolyGhost79 were still to mount their assaults on pole but ultimately they would fall short, some 2.2183s and 2.620s respectively.  The rest of the field was spread evenly back to BreakerMorant at the tail end, crossing the line in 1:48.176. 107% was 1:46.726.</p>
<p>As the pack got away the Group Force India in second place made it’s usual stunning getaway and had it’s nose ahead into turn 1.  Flouncy backed off, not wanting to lose the championship on the first corner, while TurrbalTerror kept it wide not wanting to get in the way of a potentially epic battle.  Atomic Lambo saw his gap and took it, through into second place at turn two, leaving TurrbalTerror and HolyGhost79 in to start the battle for the bottom podium position.</p>
<p>A few laps in and HolyGhost79 went past TurrbalTerror after he ran it wide on Turn 17 and stayed off track while HolyGhost79 went past.  Turrbal clawed back the 3 second gap by the next lap and the dicing between himself, HolyGhost79 and Atomic Lambo was back on, continuing past the first round of pit stops which all three took at the end of lap 7.  The on track battle helped Flouncy to extend his lead to comfortable 15 seconds by the middle of the race and it seemed the race was done and dusted.</p>
<p>HolyGhost79 was not going to give up that easily and through the second half of the race he reduced the gap down to a visible 2.6s.  Ultimately the race long battle he fought with his car beat him, as he spun on the final lap, preventing any possible final confrontation and putting the championship winner beyond doubt.</p>
<p>Well done to Flouncy on another spectacular title win.  What do the other drivers have to do to overcome this phenom.</p>]]></bodyText>
