          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><strong>1st - Flouncy - Ferrari</strong><br />Controlled and measured drive. Handled the first corner setback well and set himself up for a comfortable win with good strategy and consistent pace. Never really looked troubled.<br /><br /><strong>2nd - Atomic Lambo - Lotus-Renault</strong><br />A solid drive. Kept out of trouble, was mistake free, but just didn't quite have the overall pace that the Ferrari did. Suffered some tire degradation during the first stint that allowed Flouncy to catch up, but solid after that. Gave the Ferrari a small scare during the second stint, as well as an incident with 3rd place ET-Rom, but overall a good drive.<br /><br /><strong>3rd - ET-ROM - Mercedes</strong><br />The surprise package of the new season so far. Vastly improved over the testing break, ET was perhaps the dark horse to shake things up and indeed he did. Putting the Mercedes on pole, all be it by the smallest of margins to claim is maiden pole. Got away well at the start and built and sustained a solid lead. By the second stint the race win was less likely, however second was well within grasp but a mistake into the last turn would see the Renault of Lambo steal the position. Regardless a stunning podium and only his 3rd so far. We are sure we'll see more.<br /><br /><strong>4th - roxas3sora3 - Williams</strong><br />Perhaps a vote for drive of the round. A solid drive from the Williams driver saw a recovery from 7th on the grid to finishing 4th, just off the podium. Keeping relatively out of trouble and avoiding some of the chaos behind, roxas put in a solid drive to round out the top 4. Vastly improved over last season, another young talent to watch.<br /><br /><strong>5th - HOLYGHOST79 - Lotus</strong><br />Not the best start to a season from the Lotus driver, give his explosive start to season 3 and missing out on the drivers championship by only 16 points. A relatively disappointing race give he was an early favorite amongst the book makers. A number of mistakes saw last seasons runner up tangle with a number of drivers. A number of pundits criticized his pre-season preparation, and perhaps rightfully so. He never looked comfortable and number of errors was telling. A 20 second penalty for his hit on TurrbalTerror was warranted. Hopefully he bounces back next race in Malaysia.<br /><br /><strong>6th - CruiserComet - Lotus-Renault</strong><br />A good start to the season for the new Lotus-Renault drive. Steep learning curve but has plenty of potential. Qualified a solid 6th place and through patience was rewarded with 6th finishing ahead above the highly rated Eradicator and TurrbalTerror. Stayed out of relative trouble, one or two mistakes, but a good start to the season and critical points for the constructors championship.<br /><br /><strong>7th - Eradicator84 - Williams</strong><br />After a season hiatus Eradicator was back driving for Williams. Eradicators last race was round 19 of season two, so there was alot of interest to see how he'd fair after a season out of the sport. Qualifying a solid 7th considering, his race was also solid, if somewhat unspectacular. As he gets up to speed he will be very dangerous. A good points haul for Williams with both cars finishing the race.<br /><br /><strong>8th - TurrbalTerror - McLaren</strong><br />One of the early favorites having completed extensive pre-season testing, however was mared by bad luck and a number of run ins. Early contact with Ghost saw his race ruined and it appeared after that the McLaren driver never got back on song. However he was quick and bolting on the softs near the end of the race, he achieved the fastest lap dipping into the 1:23's albeit finishing 2 laps down.<br /><br /><strong>9th - BreakerMorant - Ferrari</strong><br />Perhaps one to forget for the Ferrari sister car, an improved start to the championship was on the cards after toiling away last season for experience. Qualified 10th on the grid, and made solid ground on the much more experienced Lotus driver of Fredzfrog. However 9th is a solid result and a foundation on which to build on and 2 important points in constructors championship.<br /><br /><strong>DNF - Fredzfrog - Lotus</strong><br />A very disappointing start to the season for the number 2 lotus driver. Showed promise in the later rounds of season 3, and now has the experience, but yet to show it on the track. Melbourne suits the driver and a solid 9th in qualifying was a solid start, however 7th or higher wasn't out of reach. Finished 4 laps down. Will want to forget this race.<br /><br /><strong>Retired - st8smn350 - Red Bull</strong><br />Unfortunately poor reliability saw the Red Bull rookie unable to finish the race as his RB7 ground to a halt on lap 5 with lap issues. Something we hope will be rectified next week in Malaysia.<br /><br /><strong>Retired - NIGHTKID2 - Sauber</strong><br />The second of the retires, a blown engine unfortunately ended the second of the rookies race on lap 29. <br /><br /><strong>Qualifying Lap</strong><br />ET ROM - 1:22.960<br /><strong>Fastest Lap</strong><br />TurrbalTerror - 1:23.452</p>
<p><strong>Drive of the day</strong> is always a tough one, because naturally it's hard to past the winning driver.  While Flouncy put in a fantastic recovery driver to take the win, my driver of the day goes to ET Rom, off the back of a huge improvement since initial off season practice for season 4. </p>
<p>We can't always put in brilliant efforts all the time, so <strong>Donkey of the Race</strong> is awarded to the driver who most completely muffed his race up or muffed it up for others around him.  As with Driver of the Race, Donkey of the race considers where the driver should have finished had not he driven like such an ass.  While HolyGhost79's general lack of race pace and consistency as well as causing an accident on Lap 1 that interfered with a few drivers races, make him a candidate, TurrbalTerror wins the award for the following assine actions:</p>
<ul>
<li>Stalling coming out of the pits in qualifying</li>
<li>Crashing into HolyGhost79 on lap 1</li>
<li>Getting 3 drive through penalties</li>
<li>Breaking his nose on entry to the pitlane</li>
<li>Missing the pitlane on one attempt, when following Eradicator84</li>
</ul>
<p>All in light of setting the race fastest lap and nearly the pole time on prime tyres, makes him the biggest donkey of the race.</p>]]></bodyText>
