        <Race id="1701" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="2" createDate="2011-10-16T21:50:39" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:51" nodeName="Round 2 Malaysia" urlName="round-2-malaysia" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1701" isDoc="">
          <race>63</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>A record number of 15 drivers lined up for the Malaysian qualifying and race for Season 4.  Following an unprecendent level of pre-race testing and information sharing between team mates, hopes for all drivers were running high.  The championship is fast become more than a quick race between a few like minded individuals.  Round 2 of Season 4 built on the foundations of a large field at Round 1, to make this a true event, and the tensions and intensity during the 28 lap reflected this.</p>
<p>As testing indicated, McLaren were going to have a fast car for this race, and they didn't disappoint.  bobaj0r secured his first pole position of the season and his first since Turkey Season 3, with a massive half second gap over Atomic Lambo.  The second row of the grid was occuppied by the other McLaren driver, TurrbalTerror, and HolyGhost79, driving for Lotus.</p>
<p>The surprise of qualifying was double world champion and season 4 points leader Flouncy who started in his lowest grid position ever, sixth place, 1 behind the Mercedes of ET Rom.</p>
<p>With such a shake up of the grid, the race was looking to be very interesting and held the lure of turning the pionts table upside down.  A the grid got away and the front runners engaged their KERS to clear the pack, a fast starting Flouncy stuck his nose of the inside of 5th place only to be struck from behind, being sent into multiple spins before being hit again by two more cars.  Flouncy's scream through the team radio evident of the high tensions this event was producing and that even after two titles, his motivation to win is as high as ever.  Something he'd need from 13th position.</p>
<p>No such bad luch fell bobaj0r, who on option tyres pulled away from the pack as if they were standing still, with pace no one, not even Atomic Lambo had answer for.  As the field settled down, the front pack looked like: bobaj0r, Atomic Lambo, ET Rom, TurrbalTerror, and HolyGhost79, with the pack spreading out as every lap passed.  The first battle, between ET Rom, TurrbalTerror, and HolyGhost79 was hard fought right up until the first round of pitstops, where TurrbalTerror and then a lap later ET Rom pitted, leaving HolyGhost79 with a few laps of trouble free running.</p>
<p>As this battle warred on Flouncy was quietly making his way up through the pack.</p>
<p>Once the first round of pitstops had been completed by all runners, the front still looked the same, with bobaj0r holding a comfortable lead over Atomic Lambo, and then a gap back to the battle for 4way battle for third between HolyGhost79, Eradicator84, ET Rom and TurrbalTerror.  This remained the front pack battle for the majority of the race, with only HolyGhosts79's contact of his front right with TurrbalTerror's left rear on turn 14, which put him into a spin, allowing TurrbalTerror to consolidate the final podium position. </p>
<p>McLaren take constructors honours, with 1st and 3rd places, boosting them up to 2nd place in constructors, with Atomic Lambo leading the title after two 2nd place finishes.</p>
<p>There were a number of incidents through out the race, the most notorius driver being NIGHTKID2.  While he managed to keep out of the way on a number of occasions, a few incidents when in the proximity of more experienced drivers, particularly Flouncy cost other competitors important race points.  Another contender for <strong>Donkey of the Race</strong> was Eradicator84, who otherwise had a good race, until he overtook HolyGhost79 on the inside of turn 15 on his way to an immediate pitstop.  Shooting up the inside of HolyGhost79 and then across the race track rather than left and up the inside down the straight cause a collision that sent HolyGhost79 into a spin and slide across the grass.</p>
<p><strong>Drive of the Race</strong> definitely goes to bobaj0r.  A dominating qualifying laying the foundation for untouchable race pace, with only one spin coming out of the pits on cold primes after his first stop, marring what would otherwise be a perfect record.</p>
<h2>How they fared</h2>
<p><strong>1st - bobaj0r - McLaren</strong><br />Completely dominated the round from start to finish. A stunning qualifying lap some 4 tenths faster than the Renault of Lambo. Pulled away at the start of the race and never looked back. Had a small scare after the first set of pit stops, but never looked like giving the win away, in the end comfortably pulling away and finishing a good 25 seconds in front of Lambo. Definitely the drive of the round.<br /><br /><strong>2nd - Lambo - Lotus-Renault</strong><br />Another solid drive from the number one at Renault. Solid pace in qualifying, but just didn't quite have the speed in the race to challenge the McLaren of bobaj0r. Stayed out of trouble and didn't put a foot wrong. Had a nice tangle with ghost after the second pits but realistically the Lotus was on a different strategy. Finished 25+ seconds down, but 20 odd in front of the next McLaren. Renault go into China full of confidence and suddenly leading both the drivers and constructors.<br /><br /><strong>3rd - TurrbalTerror - McLaren</strong><br />Solid race, but slightly off the pace in qualifying after encouraging times set in practice, the McLaren driver spent alot of time dicing with the Lotus of HOLYGHOST79 and the Mercedes of ET ROM which most likely compromised his race in chasing after the Renault of Lambo. However solid points and critical for the drivers and constructors championship. <br /><br /><strong>4th - HOLYGHOST79 - Lotus</strong><br />Showed decent pace in the race, but a number of mistakes and accidents proved to halt his charge for what looked like a possible podium. Went against the pattern in terms of tire strategy opting to qualify on primes rather than options. Spent some time behind the McLaren of TurrbalTerror and showed good pace despite being on the harder tire. However mistakes cost Ghost and a spin after tagging the back of the McLaren of TurrbalTerror caused a spin losing a place and any chance of a podium. Several laps later another incident with the Torro Rosso of Fredzfrog resulted in loosing an en-plate. Much improved over Melbourne, however will want to work on building some confidence and consistency. Looking for more from the Lotus driver in China.<br /><br /><strong>5th - ET ROM au - Mercedes</strong><br />After a solid podium at Melbourne the Mercedes driver would be looking to build on his promising start to the season. Qualifying he was slightly off the front row times, but had excellent pace come race. Had a great start shooting up to third by the first corner, but was slowly reeled in by the better pace of the McLaren of TurrbalTerror. Diced with Ghost for a few laps but all things considering 5th was a good result and he'll be looking to build on that for China. Goes into china only 6 points behind Flouncy so will want to look at challenging the front runners soon.<br /><br /><strong>6th - Eradicator84 - Williams</strong><br />Slowly getting back into rythm after a season hiatus, the Williams driver would want to look at building on his relatively solid start to the season. Other than a small tangle with Ghost when trying to enter the pits during his 2nd pit, the Williams driver kept mostly to himself and put in a solid result. After qualifying 7th just behind the Ferrari of Flouncy, he was able to gain a place and actually set decent laps. Will want to slowly work his way back up the grid.<br /><br /><strong>7th - Flouncy - Ferrari</strong><br />His worst result to date and one that the two time champion will want to forget. Had a horrid time in qualifying with issues despite solid practice pace and lost out badly at the start being tagged multiple times dropping him well down the order. Suffered a puncture before his first stop and at the worst place on the track just after the pit entrance. Despite the horrid weekend, he only lies 5 points off Lambo and with China a happy hunting ground will look to bounce back.<br /><br /><strong>8th - CruiserComet - Lotus-Renault</strong><br />Another solid race from the quickly improving Renault driver. Didn't have the best qualifying, setting a time some 8 seconds off the pace, however his race pace was good and was able to jump both roxas and notjedi and score 2 important points. Will want to build on that for China to help Renault in the constructors championship.<br /><br /><strong>9th - roxas3sora3 - Williams</strong><br />Slightly disappointing race for the Williams driver. Set a good time in qualifying to put the Williams right behind the sister car in 8th on the grid. Lost out to CruiserComet in the end however he showed the Willaims had good pace setting a 1:32 which was two seconds faster than the Renault, however inconsistency was a problem, but still promising improvements. Will want to be challenging the mid field at China.<br /><br /><strong>10th - BreakerMorant - Ferrari</strong><br />Second consecutive points finish, all be it a few laps down and one place worse then Melbourne. However sometimes finishing the race is more important and he's shown clear improvement slowly getting faster and faster over the race distance. Will want to translate this slow rise in performance with more solid points to help Ferrari in the constructors race. <br /><br /><strong>11th - Fredzfrog - Lotus</strong><br />Just finishing out side the points again Fredzfrog can be slightly disappointed being beaten out by the much less experienced BreakerMorant. A lack of pre-race practice was telling with the Lotus driver only slightly in front of the second Ferrari. A miss understanding with the Lotus of Ghost the most interesting aspect of the race. Actually set a better fast lap then the 2nd Ferrari but couldn't be consistent.<br /><br /><strong>12th - NIGHTKID2 - Sauber</strong><br />Another driver setting a faster lap in race than in qualifying. Finished a few laps down, and at times had trouble negotiating the blue flags, but overall experience is important and after not finishing at all in Melbourne will want to build and grow on this experience.<br /><br /><strong>13th - st8smn350 - Red Bull</strong><br />Actually was close to the pace in qualifying with the back markers. Could have started as high as 11 with a cleaner lap. Was let down by issues which severely affected his race. Wasn't able to really challenge but did finish the race. More experience under the belt in which to build on.<br /><br /><strong>14th - notjedi - Red Bull</strong><br />Disappointing result considering his qualifying pace. Had all sorts of issues in race and will want to forget and move onto China.<br /><br /><strong>DNF - MaverickROM - Mercedes</strong><br />Was severely hindered by a lack of race preparation which was telling setting the slowest qualifying time that was not in relation to the drivers talent. Will want to forget this round and focus on a better preparation for China.</p>]]></bodyText>
