        <Race id="1721" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="3" createDate="2011-10-23T22:29:59" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:51" nodeName="Round 3 China" urlName="round-3-china" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1721" isDoc="">
          <race>64</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Shanghai saw our third winner from three races this season.  The qualifying session was wet, neutralising the raw pace the McLarens were expected to have over a single lap.  What we saw instead was our first wet session of the season and a Flouncy pole position be nearly half a second. </p>
<p>The top qualifiers were separated by 1 second from 1st down to fifth, with bobaj0r lining up in fifth place, 0.4s behind his McLaren teammate, who had run out of fuel near the end of his hot lap, preventing would could have been pole position.  The rest of the grid was evenly spaced out down to 12th position, with the 13th place getter and new comer, Modz85, being disqualified for leaving the track early.</p>
<p>Race day was cloudy but with 8% chance of rain, the rain held off for the entire race and we were blessed with a great race a dominant performance by Lambo, who after 2 second places in the last 2 races, improved his position one more to reach the top step of the podium. </p>
<p>Off the line, Atomic Lambo and Flouncy got off well and pushed each other hard, opening a small gap over HolyGhost79 who was being hounded by the two McLaren boys, running nose to tail.  After trying to pass HolyGhost79 for 4 laps, TurrbalTerror moved over for this teammate to have a shot, and on lap 7 he pitted for new Primes tires.  On Lap 8 bobaj0r got by HolyGhost79 for second, after Flouncy spun back to fourth at turn 3 lap 7.</p>
<p>Some of the great battles on track this race:</p>
<ul>
<li>Atomic Lambo v Flouncy</li>
<li>HolyGhost79 v TurrbalTerror</li>
<li>HolyGhost79 v bobajor</li>
<li>Flouncy v TurrbalTerror</li>
<li>ET Rom v TurrbalTerror</li>
<li>CruiserComent v roxas3sora3</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>1st - Lambo - Lotus-Renault</strong><br />Completely dominated the race from start to finish. Qualifying was tricky with the wet conditions with the top 3 only separated by only 4 tenths of a second, however a fantastic start saw the Renault jump Ghost at the start and then pass the Ferrari on the back straight before the end of the first lap. From then on showed great pace and made a two stop strategy work well. Highly deserved his first race win of season 4.<br /><br /><strong>2nd - bobaj0r - McLaren</strong><br />Another solid drive from the Mclaren driver. A great recovery from 5th on the grid with the only error choosing a double prime tire strategy. Could have challenged for the win otherwise. Tangled with Ghost for many laps and showed good pace during the last stint however just ran out of laps. In dangerous looking form and with the Championship leader absent for the next round in Istanbul, we could be see a new championship leader next round.<br /><br /><strong>3rd - Flouncy - Ferrari</strong><br />Will consider this a disappointing race despite a spirited fight back to steal 3rd place from the Lotus of Ghost. Was amongst the favourites for this race with blistering pace set during pre-practice sessions and when he put the Ferrari on pole in wet and difficult conditions, the race win seems likely. However a slow start and a mistake on lap 4 he never was able to get on song and was well off the pace. The hot favourite at the start of the year now sees himself 15 points off the Renault. However with lots of racing left and the absence of Lambo in the next round we could still see some surprises.<br /><br /><strong>4th - HOLYGHOST79 - Lotus</strong><br />Lotus will walk away from this race knowing that a botched tire strategy cost them a likely podium. The Lotus started with an aggressive race approach starting on the prime tire after qualifying 2nd in the wet conditions. However lost out badly at the start being passed quickly by Lambo and bobaj0r. Spent alot of time battling bobaj0r and pitted very early on lap 11 for option tires with 17 laps to go. Eventually had to pit again on lap 22 for another set of option tires losing out to Ben but comfortably ahead of ET ROM au. Will rue an opportunity lost and will desperately want a good result in Istanbul to get his season back on track.<br /><br /><strong>5th - ET ROM au - Mercedes</strong><br />His second consecutive 5th place was one of slight frustration. Slightly off the pace in both qualifying and in the race it looked unlikely the Mercedes was going to challenge the front runners, but with plenty of points to play for in the constructors an important result nevertheless. Stayed pretty much out of trouble only making one or two mistakes and was able to capitalise on TurrbalTerrors spin but will want to try and regain some of that early season form. <br /><br /><strong>6th - TurrbalTerror - McLaren</strong><br />Solid race, but no doubt will be slightly disappointed that he wasn't challenging for a podium. Showed excellent pace during practice especially one runs on the prime tire. Qualified fourth in difficult conditions and had good battles with Flouncy and Ghost. However a mistake on Lap 20 with a spin that resulted in a damaged nose cost him points as the McLaren pitted for a new nose and lost a place to ET ROM. Set the fastest lap which is a small consolation, but will want to be challenging for podiums again in the next race to get his title challenge going and with McLaren only 7 points off in the constructors race.<br /><br /><strong>7th - NightKid2 - Sauber</strong><br />The new rookie backed up his best qualifying performance with his first Atomic F1 points and finished a respectable 8th. Slowly on the improvement, will want to build on this experience and chase down Williams in the constructors race.<br /><br /><strong>8th - CruiserComet - Lotus-Renault</strong><br />Another solid race from the quickly improving Renault driver. Very respectable in qualifying will want to start challenging the mid field runners to help in the constructors battle.<br /><br /><strong>9th - roxas3sora3 - Williams</strong><br />Slightly disappointing race for the Williams driver. Set a good time in qualifying especially in difficult conditions. Lost out to CruiserComet in the end but lacked some race pace in the end being some 4 seconds off the pace, however finished much higher then his highly rated team-mate. Will want to be back challenging the mid field at Istanbul.<br /><br /><strong>10th - BreakerMorant - Ferrari</strong><br />Three consecutive points finish, all be it a few laps down and one place worse then Melbourne. China was clearly not his best track and surprisingly set the same qualifying time in the wet as he did in race. Plenty to work on from here, but will want to try and start moving up the order to secure more points for the constructors championship.<br /><br /><strong>11th - st8smn350 - Red Bull</strong><br />Slowly on the improvement and just out of the points, unfortunately spent much of the race letting faster cars through. Is slowly finding his feat and with more practice will want to start challenging the the saubers.<br /><br /><strong>12th - Eradicator84 - Williams</strong><br />Little was heard or seen of the Williams driver. Probably a compromised race preparation. Should have been much high up the grid and will want to improve before next weekends race.</p>]]></bodyText>
