        <Race id="1746" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="4" createDate="2011-10-30T19:50:13" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:51" nodeName="Round 4 Turkey" urlName="round-4-turkey" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1746" isDoc="">
          <race>65</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Increasing intensity at Turkey saw a dramatic grid and a close race, depsite the points leader, Atomic Lambo, missing the round.</p>
<p>Pole position went to bobaj0r, with TurrbalTerror in the sister McLaren in second place, six hundredths back. There was a 0.3 second gap to third but first through to fifth were seperated by only a second.  NightKid2 put in a stellar performance to be 0.7s off the pace in fifth place.  An impressive effort.</p>
<p>Race day saw a 9% chance of rain, with cloudy skies.  As most of the field got away, except for a bogged down TurrbalTerror, doing his best Mark Webber impersonation, Flouncy found the holeshot and took it spearing from 4th into the race lead, as the dramatic onboard footage from TurrbalTerror shows.  Turn one wasn't without further incident though as NightKid2 also looked to capitalise and optimistically tried to go three wide through turn one, between TurrbalTerror on the inside and Eradicator84 on the outside.  The move was never going to stick and while TurrbalTerror and Eradicator84 both gave the hard-charger room, he touched TurrbalTerror and spun, to be collected by BreakerMorant.</p>
<p>Flouncy, bobaj0r, and Eradicator84 pulled a mini gap over TurrbalTerror, ET ROM, HolyGhost79, and the improving roxas3sora3, as TurrbalTerror struggled through turn 8.  By the last few corners of the track, TurrbalTerror had caught them back again and was attempting to pass Flouncy.  A KERS assisted move he later pulled off on the exit of the final turn. </p>
<p>The two battled closely for the next few laps, as ET Rom and HolyGhost79 started to back up behind them, a train forming.  TurrbalTerror pulled left to look for a gap to pass Flouncy on the inside of turn 1, and thought better of it pulling back in behind him.  It was enough to break the rythm and ET Rom tapped TurrbalTerror into the turn, and Flouncy was away down the track.</p>
<p>TurrablTerror, ET Rom, with HolyGhost79 sitting patient behind, then battled it out, ET Rom getting past when TurrbalTerror braked earlier than the following car expected and was pushed offline.  A few laps later, on lap 6 ET ROM spun on the exit of turn 7 and speared across the nose of TurrbalTerror, luckily not taking them both out but certainly ruining ET Rom's chance of a podium, when he showed good speed.  With that collision HolyGhost79 made a clean pass on both of them and never looked back.</p>
<p>At the first round of pitstops the two McLarens were queued in the pits, losing TurrbalTerror further time as he waited for his tires to be brought out.  McLaren have since evaluated their pit stop protocols and have promised to communicate better in future races.</p>
<p>Up front bobaj0r and Eradicator84 were dicing it out when bobaj0r's wheel came off, resulting in a spin, from which he would recover.</p>
<p>Further down the pack NightKid2 was recovering strongly and roxas3sora3 was putting in a solid drive, well into the midfield battle between ET Rom and TurrbalTerror.  Although his ECU did seem to be running in fuel conservation mode, which would explain his atrocious lack of top speed, making him a sitting duck on down the straights.</p>
<p>ET Roms' spinning activities were far from over after the first incident, after racing incidents with roxas3sora3 sent him into a spin and a far to optimistic attempt by NightKid2 also pushed him off, as it looked like the later driver attempted to drive right through him.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>bobaj0r<br /></strong>Another dominant drive from the Brisbane based driver, leading from pole position and fighting back after his wheel fell off. Also setting fastest race lap toward the end of the race.</p>
<p><strong>Eradicator84<br /></strong>Drove an extremely strong race from third on the grid into second place, pushing bobaj0r hard all the way.</p>
<p><strong>HolyGhost79<br /></strong>Despite connection performance problems forcing him to adjust his style, he implemented a prime tires first strategy that paid off, allowing an error free drive from 7th to 3rd</p>
<p><strong>Flouncy<br /></strong>The double champion again didn't seem to have the ultimate pace but made up for a qualifying result that was lower than he expected by having the best start of the year, fourth to first on the first corner.  He may have been able to achieve more if not battling it out with TurrbalTerror for the opening laps.</p>
<p><strong>TurrbalTerror<br /></strong>Qualified well but made a miserable start and was bullied around for the first few laps.   Lacked the ultimate pace of the front runners, despite running the same setup as bobaj0r.  Lost the most places in the race, dropping from 2nd to 5th by race end.  His fastest lap, nearly a full second slower than his teammate and a few others indicated his lack of race pace.</p>
<p><strong>NightKid2<br /></strong>Put in a solid qualifying performance, his best to date, but overly optimistic passing moves cost him and the cars he was involved with.  When he learns how to race in close promixity with others, he'll be a force to be reckoned with.</p>
<p><strong>ET Rom_au<br /></strong>Qualified nearly two seconds off the pace but put in a stronger race effort than his pace indicated.  Battled with TurrbalTerror for a good portion of the race.  Mistakes and collisions, some his own fault, some no fault of his own cost him time and race results.</p>
<p><strong>roxas3sora3<br /></strong>Race results did not justly reward his performance.  Drove one of his best races to date, battling well with those around him.  Race fastest lap was only a tenth slower than his qualifying lap, showing he improved as he drove on.  Wrong fuel setting cost him performance and results.  He performed admirably for Williams and will be looking to step it up for Spain in a weeks time.</p>
<p><strong>CruiserComet</strong><br />Lagging issues hampered his performance but he kept his nose clean and brought the car home in the points.  A poor weekend for Renault and he no doubt missed his team leaders influence.</p>
<p><strong>BreakerMorant</strong><br />Drove a solid race but finished where he started.  While his results may not reflect it, his race performances are improving and Ferrari have more to look forward to in Spain.</p>
<p><strong>Fredzfrog<br /></strong>Another driver who put in a solid effort. Fredzfrog continues to inspire underdogs around the world with his determined drives despite lack of pace.  He avoided faster cars without fuss.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Drive of the Race</strong>: It's hard to go past bobaj0r, but drive of the race goes to Eradicator84 for pushing the McLaren hard and making up places on his start position</p>]]></bodyText>
