          <race>67</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>The Monaco Atomic F1 Grand Prix was never going to dissapoint.  The field got a taste of what to expect in the race with a half completed "warm up" qualifying session which saw Atomic Lambo go fastest on a 1:09.9, but not all the fastest drviers had set a time.  The dropout of Eradicator84 caused a restart, although he was later to drop out again in the following qualifying session.</p>
<p>Once the final qualifying session opened, so did the heavens and we had what all the drivers feared, a wet tract at Monaco.  Atomic Lambo set the fastest lap, followed by bobaj0r and TurrbalTerror, the Lotus Renault breaking the run of front row lock-outs the McLaren have recently been enjoying.</p>
<p><strong>1st - HolyGhost79</strong> <strong>- Team Lotus</strong><br />In an event that we won't see again for long while, HolyGhost79 took advantage of the misfortune of bobaj0r and Atomic Lambo to cut his way through the grid, from last place, in a near faultless drive.<strong>﻿</strong></p>
<p><strong>2nd - Flouncy - Ferrari<br /></strong>The rain didn't suit the double world champion as lined up 4th on the grid, some 2.1 seconds back from the pole. He battled hard with TurrbalTerror on a few occasions, and ran through the pits more than he needed to after damaging front wings.  Had he qualified in front of TurrbalTerror he may have had the pace for the race win.</p>
<p><strong>3rd - TurrbalTerror - McLaren<br /></strong>Finished where he started, just without the two drives in front he expected.  Drove a decent race to lead from lap 8 to lap 25 when built up a 20 second lead to 2nd place.  Was spun on the first lap by Flouncy which cost him 12 seconds.  Had a few problems with backmarkers at critical moments and slightly damaged the front wing a few times, spending 50% of the managing a damaging nose.  Finished about where he expected.</p>
<p><strong>4th - bobaj0r - ﻿McLaren<br /></strong>Finishing behind his teammate for the first time this season, bobajor had  race he'd rather forget but still managed a fourth position.  He was spun on the first lap after a tap from Atomic Lambo, resulting in a radio outburst we haven't heard since ET Rom in Turkey last week.  He was recovering well before suffering a puncture not long after his 2nd pitstop.  Gutted to have finished in his worst position fo the year and will be champing at the bit to prove he can do it at his bogey track in Canada.</p>
<p><strong>5th - ET ROM au - Mercedes<br /></strong>Had a quiet race meet on his way to 5th place after being lapped by the leaders.  He'll be wanting to increase his pace on Montreal although he finished as first of the rest and probably finished higher than he would have if not for Atomic Lambo's retirement.</p>
<p><strong>6th - Modz85 - Sauber<br /></strong>Finally his car managed to not let him down the qualify sessions and Modz joined for his first complete race with Atomic F1.  He qualified a fantastic 5th considering his rookie status and brought it home in 6th place albiet a lap down.  His performance was solid and drove enough to keep out of the eye of the stewards.</p>
<p><strong>7th - st8smn350 - Toros Rosso<br /></strong>Finished in his best position yet and performed admirably pace wise ﻿with a solid race fastest lap time.  Is starting to show some of the pre-season form he had prior to his disconnection problems. st8smn350 will be looking forward to a further improved positions in Canada.</p>
<p><strong>8th - roxas3sora3 - Williams</strong><br />Following the loss of his teammate it was up to sora3 to bring it home for the team from Grove.  Only making up one place from the grid, he'll be wanting to up his speed and establish himself as a front running midrunner.</p>
<p><strong>DSQ - Atomic Lambo - Lotus Renault<br /></strong>A race Lambo will definitely want to forget, when a race win was lost to him through now fault of his own.  Lambo pressed on after a turn 1 incident with bobaj0r and capitalised on the TurrbalTerror and Flouncy contact as they battled for second place, allowing his lead to instantly jump to 13.5 seconds by the end of the second lap.</p>
<p><strong>DSQ - CruiserComent - Lotus Renault<br /></strong>Really not a race that Lotus Renault want to revisit.  Battling with intermittent connection problems, he lost his front wing when bobaj0r passed and it was enough to force him to park the car.</p>
<p><strong>DSQ - FredzFrogz - Toro Rosso<br /></strong>Another race to forget for Fredzfrogz.  Car problems caused his early retirement but he struggled for pace in all sessions.﻿</p>]]></bodyText>
