        <Race id="1792" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="7" createDate="2011-11-21T07:39:24" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:52" nodeName="Round 7 Canada" urlName="round-7-canada" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1792" isDoc="">
          <race>68</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Canada was expected to be a closely faught affair between bobaj0r and Atomic Lambo, and in the end, that's exactly what it was.</p>
<p>Pole position went to bobaj0r with a fine drive, to beat Atomic Lambo by 0.2 seconds, with TurrbalTerror and Flouncy the other drivers to go under 70 seconds.  That was after the qualifying restart caused by FredzFrogz being disqualified for heavily crashing in game (as opposed to his computer crashing).</p>
<p>The race got underway with bobaj0r falling victim to a tyre bug that robbed him of all grip from the start of the race.  The other McLaren of TurrbalTerror also got punted off track by a blinking car and suddenly both McLarens were back of the pack.  Fortunately for them, but less fortunate for race leader Atomic Lambo, half the field suffered disconnection problems and the race was restarted, this time with a random grid.</p>
<p>The restart saw roxas3sora3 in pole, with HolyGhost79 and fredzfrog up the front too.  The McLarens lined up 5th and 6th with Atomic Lambo and Flouncy further toward the back of the pack.  Leggards pick had his race work cut out of him if he was to be victorious.</p>
<p>The start was a bit messy but after a few laps bobaj0r was in the lead and TurrbalTerror in second place, albiet with a broken wing.  Fast rising through the pack was Atomic Lambo and Flouncy. Before the first round of stops the Renault driver had the McLaren number 2 and was darting back and forward looking for a way past.  With team orders in full swing the McLaren driver made his car about 2 track widths wide as he struggled with a very pacey Atomic Lambo and a broken front wing on his own car.  Try as Atomic Lambo might, he uncharacteriscally got the gearing wrong and lacked the pace down the main back straight.  TurrbalTerror only had to save his KERS for that part of the circuit and the Renault had no answer. And save his KERS he did.  Eventually the first round of stops came and TurrbalTerror dived into the pits, giving Atomic Lambo a chance to build a gap before he too had to pit. </p>
<p>Flash forward toward the end of the race and Atomic Lambo passed for the lead with only a few laps remaining.  It was close but again his lack of top end speed let him down as bobaj0r got a bite of KERS and DRS to breeze by the Renault driver on the last corner of the race. </p>]]></bodyText>
