        <Race id="1813" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="8" createDate="2011-11-28T08:57:03" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:52" nodeName="Round 8 Europe" urlName="round-8-europe" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1813" isDoc="">
          <race>69</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>The first race with Patch 2 for F1 2011 and things did not go smoothly.  Mainly the enhancements to the networking code made the racing worst. Initial testing with a few players was good, but with 13, it didn't go so well and as soon as anyone spoke everyone suffered massive frame rate drop that made the cars undriveable.  The race was restarted with everyone muting everyone else.</p>
<p>bobaj0r led from pole, followed by Flouncy, Modz85 and TurrbalTerror. A collision at turn 1 caused by ET Rom put Flouncy and Modz out of the running and opened a gap for Atomic Lambo to take second place, from fifth on the grid.  The race was eventually won by bobaj0r, who for the most part kept his nose clean while others faltered, allowing him to build a lead that could not be lost.</p>
<p><strong>1st - bobaj0r<br /></strong>Drove another near error free race, nearly lost 1st place to the faster at the sister McLaren, but defended strategically.  The win was all but sealed when TurrbalTerror lost the rear-end on lap 18 and received a drive through.</p>
<p><strong>2nd - TurrbalTerror<br /></strong>Drove hard to take 2nd place and might have won if not for a few slips, some of his own doing and some by others.  Had clear pace over the non-Mclaren cars and made the best of Flouncy being mid-field.</p>
<p><strong>3rd - Atomic Lambo<br /></strong>Unfortunate not to have finished in second place, losing out halfway along the last lap and coming to a near halt, or so it would seem.  Battled hard and probably had a few mistakes that kept him down.</p>
<p><strong>4th - HolyGhost79<br /></strong>Started near the back of the pack but like Monaco made good ground again when accidents happened further up the order.  Lacked outright pace to challenge for the podium but must be satisfied with the fourth place. It could have been worse.</p>
<p><strong>5th - Eradicator84</strong><br />Drove a good race, challenging for the top spots early on but also lacked overall pace, his fastest lap 2.6 seconds off.</p>
<p><strong>6th - Flouncy<br /></strong>Had plenty to be optimistic about on the grid, with a solid second place start.  Was punted off track early and never recovered.  From there he couldn't show his true pace, or avoid further incidents.</p>
<p><strong>7th - Modz85<br /></strong>Started 3rd but was effected by first lap drama.  The game seemed to place him at a different place on the track to what others saw.  Set the fourth fastest race lap. A good effort.</p>
<p><strong>8th - ET Rom<br /></strong>Not as good as it could have been, ET never showed fantastic pace and finished consistent with his overall race fastest lap.  Involved in an unneccessary incident on lap 1.</p>
<p><strong>9th - roxas3sora3<br /></strong>Showed good pace in friday practice but was unable to convert that to the race pace of this teammate. </p>
<p><strong>10th - st8smn350<br /></strong>Had a quiet race off the radar, but getting out of the way of others when it counted.  It is expected that a lack of practice accounted for the low pace.</p>
<p><strong>DSQ - NightKid2, BreakerMorant, CruiserComet (Connections)<br /></strong></p>]]></bodyText>
