        <Race id="1829" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="9" createDate="2011-12-04T20:36:08" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:52" nodeName="Round 9 Britian" urlName="round-9-britian" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1829" isDoc="">
          <race>70</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Round 9 of season four was a closely contested affair, perhaps the closest all year.  Bobaj0r once again sat on pole position after Atomic Lambo and TurrbalTerror couldn't replicate their practice speed and also dip into the 1:26's.</p>
<p>The start saw bobaj0r and Atomic Lambo lead with a gap over about 1 second over TurrbalTerror.  Lambo got by with a move up the inside into Brooklands, which became his preffered passing place during the race, taking the lead there two more times. After the first round of pitstops on lap 6, when Lambo and bobaj0r entered the pits together, the Mclaren team turned their car around faster and bobaj0r got back in the lead, only to lose it again a few corners later on cold tyres.  Meanwhile, TurrbalTerror who pitted a lap later to avoid car stacking in the McLaren pits came out right behind the two, but lost groud on cold tyres, falling as far back as 5.7 seconds before clawing back the gap</p>
<p>By the time the second round of pitstops came, Turrbal took the lead as Lambo and bobajor again pitted together.  This time, once TurrbalTerror had pitted he came out in front of the other podium contenders, before Lambo put a move on into Brooklands for first, and bobaj0r went by a corner later, while TurrbalTerror's tyres got up to temperature. </p>
<p>The gap was much less now and the trio circulated within a second of each other before bobaj0r put a move on Lambo coming into Stowe and TurrbalTerror took advantage of the failed attempt and snuck by into second, through his favourite passing point at Vale.</p>
<p>Again the trio circulated nose to tale and TurrbalTerror took advantage of the lapped Breaker Morant to again put it up the inside into Vale and took first from Atomic Lambo.  boba also passed for 3rd, as the contact between TurrbalTerror and Atomic Lambo gave opportunity. boba got the run on TurrbalTerror and took the lead of the race with a DRS pass up the straight leading to Brooklands.</p>
<p>A lap later boba experienced technical difficulties and both TurrbalTerror and Atomic Lambo got by.  The gap was now 3.5 seconds from TurrbalTerror in the lead back to Atomic Lambo then another 7 seconds back to bobaj0r, but both Atomic Lambo and TurrbalTerror were low on fuel and had to a conservative fuel mix, while bobaj0r was not, allowing him to claw back the gap. </p>
<p>On lap 25 of 26 TurrbalTerror ran completely out of fuel and gave the victory to Lambo, not before boaj0r had caught up to be within 1.5 seconds of the lead.  Eradticat84 eventually rounded out the podium some 35 seconds back, while a distraught TurrbalTerror idled through the last lap and half to finish 6th, the last of the non lapped cars.</p>
<p>The race was again a case of he who kept his nose the cleanest won, as mistakes and problems from both McLarens thwarted their chances.</p>]]></bodyText>
