        <Race id="1841" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="10" createDate="2011-12-11T23:48:26" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:53" nodeName="Round 10 Germany" urlName="round-10-germany" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1841" isDoc="">
          <race>71</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Round 10 of Season 4, the German Grand Prix, was held at the Nurburgring this season, after being held at the Hockenhiemring for the previous 3 seasons. This presented an opportunity for the established drivers to assert themselves over their rivals, and for the new drivers to race on a level playing field, and it showed this weekend.</p>
<p>As drivers went out for qualifying it was clear the the top end hadn't changed, bobaj0r still set the fastest time, trailed by Lambo.  The surprise was TurrbalTerror, who was down in 6th position, having set his time on prime tyres.  Once out on options he was2md 0.09 seconds behind Lambo and in third position, despite being held up by NightKid2 for the entire sector 2 of his fast run.  ET ROM did extremely well to in fourth place, only half a second adrift of the established top three, with Flouncy rounding out the top 5.</p>
<p>The race loaded up wet and the during the load process Atomic Lambo dropped out.  It was decided that qualifying would be re-run when he returned.  Qualifying two got underway as a wet session and Lambo and TurrbalTerror immediately shot to the top.  Mid way through the session TurrbalTerror set his benchmark pole time, some 0.9 seconds up on 2nd, and retired to the garage for the rest of the session.  The rest of the field tried hard to match and some even going faster in sectors 1 and 3, but ultimate speed in sector 2 saw Turrbal keep the pole by 0.09s from Atomic Lambo.</p>
<p><img src="~/media/27859/2nd-quali-wet-germany_500x236.jpg"  width="500"  height="236" alt="2nd-quali-wet-germany.PNG" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"/></p>
<p>The race got underway to dry conditions, with TurrbalTerror leading from pole, until a fast starting bobaj0r pushed him wide at turn 1 and the chasing group of Flouncy and Lambo bumped him off the road and spun him round on the second last turn of the lap.</p>
<p>The podium was filled with the usual suspects.</p>
<p><strong>1st - bobaj0r</strong><br />Drove a consistently fast race out front to lead unhindered from lap 1 until the end.  A deserved winner on this new track.  Also set fastest lap on the lap immediately after TurrbalTerrors fastest lap.  Once again the Mclarens were in a league of their own for outright speed.</p>
<p><strong>2nd - Atomic Lambo</strong><br />Had a less than perfect race driving through the pits with a broken wing after collision with Eradicator84, but still finished in a deserved 2nd place.  While not the perfect race he should be satisfied with a solid 2nd and best of the rest.</p>
<p><strong>3rd - TurrbalTerror<br /></strong>bobaj0r colliding with him on turn 1 put him back to 2nd.  Flouncy colliding with him at the end of lap 1 put him 9th.  He made up ground to 8th before HolyGhost79 lost it in front of him and put him into the wall on the last turn of turn lap 2, and back to 9th again.  Moved up to 7th before getting a drive through penalty when avoiding a sliding Flouncy by going over the curb on turn 7, dropping him back to 9th.  Ran in lean fuel for the first 10 laps. Pitted on lap 7 for primes and made them last until lap 20, when he pitted for options.  With fuel to spare and extra sticky tyres he charged up the field and secured third place with a second last lap pass on Eradicator84. </p>
<p><strong>4th - Eradicator84</strong><br />Drove a solid and consistent race and would have finished on the podium if not for increased pressure from TurrbalTerror in the final laps resulted in a spin as he out-braked himself into turn 13.  Had decent race pace with the 5th fastest lap.</p>
<p><strong>5th - Flouncy</strong><br />Great race potential was thwarted by the lap 1 touch on TurrbalTerror resulting in a drive through penalty, dropping him down to 7th.  Battled with st8smn350 on lap 3 and spun, losing more ground, but was able to make it back up through the pack somewhat.  He'll want more practice ahead of the Hungoraring if he's to place on the podium.</p>
<p><strong>6th - ET Rom au</strong><br />Equalified an impressive fourth and showed competitive race times to finish despite finishing in 6th, the best of the non-race winners. ET Rom is making good progress up the grid and more consistent performances, like this, will help him.</p>
<p><strong>7th - NightKid2<br /></strong>The much maligned Sauber driver was again in the wars from a number of drivers during the race.  He battled fiercely despite a lack of overall pace, some 3.5 seconds off the leaders pace.  He'll want to cause less damage to himself and others if he wants to achieve better results.</p>
<p><strong>8th - roxas3sora3<br /></strong>Sora3 showed good pace in the rare times he had opportunity.  That he set fourth fastest race lap is testament to his improving pace.  He just needs to work on one lap speed to enable him to start higher up the grid and avoid some of the chaos that costs race time.</p>
<p><strong>9th - st8smn350</strong><br />Drove a good race to come up from the back of the grid to finish in the points.  Had a barnstorming drive in the wet qualifying to lap into 6th place, showing he has good car control. No doubt needs more track time and consistency to convert that into points.</p>
<p><strong>10th - CruiserComet<br /></strong>Cruiser appear to struggle for pace, some four seconds off the race pace and seven seconds off the qualifying pace.  That his race fastest lap was faster than his qualifying lap hints to a lack of preparation and track familiarity.</p>
<p><strong>11th - BreakerMorant<br /></strong>Again collecting a point for Ferrari, BreakerMorant was another driver to go faster in race than in practice. </p>
<p><strong>12th - Fredzfrog</strong><br />The little car that could. Fredzfrog again brought up the rear with consisent race and qualifying pace. </p>
<p><strong>DSQ - HolyGhost79<br /></strong>Have we seen the last of the Ghost?  <strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>Drive of the Race</strong><br />As always, it's hard to not give drive of the race to the winner, but this week TurrbalTerror came from 9th place and a horror first three laps, after starting from pole, to secure third place. He did it by managing his fuel and tyres and running only two stops, with only the one prime tyre run.  This enabled him a number of good fast laps on the option tyre and low fuel, which made the difference.  <strong><br /></strong></p>]]></bodyText>
