        <Race id="1850" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="11" createDate="2011-12-19T07:07:41" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:53" nodeName="Round 11 Hungary" urlName="round-11-hungary" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1850" isDoc="">
          <race>72</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Tumbleweeds could be seen blowing across the grid at Hungary prior to the race, as four of the top 5 drivers were absent from the event.  Qualifying on pole should have been a sure thing for Flouncy, but it was a hot lapping Modz85 that put his car on pole position. </p>
<p>The heavens opened for the race and that was all Flouncy needed to take the lead by the first corner, and was never headed, bringing the car home a full minute ahead of second place Eradicator84, with Modz85 slipping back to a respectable 3rd.</p>
<p>ET Rom had trouble on turn 1 of the race after Modz's poor getaway made him take evasion action from 3rd on the grid and he ran wide before hitting a spinning roxas3sora3, receiving a penalty and then being tapped by BreakerMorant on his way through.  From there, he limped home in 7th place ,his only saving grace being a thinned field.</p>]]></bodyText>
