        <Race id="1862" parentID="1652" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1197" template="1464" sortOrder="12" createDate="2012-01-09T13:22:01" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:45:53" nodeName="Round 12 Belgium" urlName="round-12-belgium" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1458,1652,1862" isDoc="">
          <race>73</race>
          <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Qualifying was an intense battle that ultimately fizzled, with large margins between 1st, 2nd, and 3rd, all of whom occupied the 1:43's.  Flouncy reigned in qualifying, where the rain did not.</p>
<p>The forecast for the race was 80% chance of rain but the drivers were greeted with at least no falling rain, although the track was still damp and spray was kicked up as the cars left the start line. The race started cleanly with a few players jockying for position and as it sorted itself out, Flouncy and Atomic Lambo opened up a gap on the rest of the field, as TurrbalTerror was bullied out of his 3rd place down to 5th, as first Eradicator84 and then ET Rom asserted their positions through the first sector corners.</p>
<p>Roxas3sora3 was disqualified on the first lap, after his computer locked up and NightKid2 drove a cautious opening lap only to be black flagged after outbraking himself into the final turn and cutting too much of the corner.</p>
<p>Once the race started to settle down, the rains came and all the players made a dive for the pits, with some choosing Full Wets and other less fortunate drivers taking the Intermediate option, only to be called back in on the next lap, when the rain fell increasingly heavy.</p>
<p>Early leader Flouncy was caught out on the first pitstop, dropping back deep into the pack and a few laps later the redoubtable-in-the-rain HolyGhost79 was into lead, chased hard by TurrbalTerror and Atomic Lambo, himself closely tailed by Eradicator84. </p>
<p>Unfortunately a handful of laps later HolyGhost79 was in the pits, where he got the tyre selection wrong and exited on the gripless intermediate tyres.  The next 10 or so laps saw TurrbalTerror lead Atomic Lambo by a small margin, as the gap yo-yo'd between 1.8 and 3.5 seconds. Meanwhile the erstwhile Flouncy made his way up through the field and had claimed fourth position.</p>
<p>After ignoring his race engineers requests for new tyres for two laps, TurrbalTerror pitted on lap 18 and selected Intermediates, hoping the easing rain would provide a drying track and he could take a massive per lap speed advantage to get back in the lead.  Unfortunately the track was too wet and he spun his car on nearly every corner of the 19th lap before putting it into the wall at the last corner and retiring from the race.</p>
<p>Ultimately Atomic Lambo again prevailed over Flouncy.  After playing the long and cautious game, he didn't need to make a final stop near the end of the race and easily able to bring the car home in first.</p>
<p>Ferrari take home the constructors win with ET ROM placing a solid 4th.</p>]]></bodyText>
