        <summary><![CDATA[Fast and often erratic.  TurrbalTerror has the ability to put his machine on pole, and set fastest laps during the race, but his qualifying performances are squandered by poor race starts, being caught in the midfield or being pushed aside by faster guys coming up the grid.  His tendancy to overdrive makes him his own worst enemy.  Not a race likely race winner but could finish on the podium if others have bad luck.]]></summary>
        <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>TurrbalTerror has held his 20 year F1 fan badge for a few years now, following the sport since the days when Alain Prost, Ayrton Senna, Nigel Mansell, and Nelson Piquet battled it out for race wins. He's played most every PC based F1 "sim" game since the PC XY, from Accolades Grand Prix, through Geoff Crammonds Grand Prix series and Codemasters F1 franchise, with most his current track time going to iRacing.</p>
<p>Ironically Season 4 has been the season where he's shown the most pace and consistency during the races, with almost 0 driving errors.&nbsp; He has, unfortunately, far and away the worst luck with fuel management and other issues relating to strategy, robbing him of a few wins and many strong podium finishes.</p>
<p>Perhaps if he spent more time practicing F1 2011 and less time maintaining atomicf1.com, he'd be more successful.&nbsp; But as his pappy said "Stick with what you're good at son.".</p>
<h3>Current Racing Rig</h3>
<p><img src="media/32629/72cwU.jpg" alt="72cwU.jpg" /></p>]]></bodyText>
