        <summary><![CDATA[BreakerMorant is a conscientious driver as well as a gentleman racer.  He's always willing to get out of the way of others when being passed, even if it's to the detriment of his own race.  As a relatively new driver, his pace is expected to improve especially now he has signed with Ferrari and will come under the tutelage of Flouncy.  A big jump in performance is expected from BreakerMorant in season 4.]]></summary>
        <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/3257/preview_400x267.jpg"  width="400"  height="267" alt="macdude-profile" style="float: right;"/></p>
<p>Details of Mac Dude’s start in racing are lost in time, though evidence of his first race first corner miss still exist. While comfortable on kiddy racing games like Wild Wild Racing on the Playstation, stepping up to grown-up persuits always seemed a bridge too far.<br /><br />Improvement was seen during those whacky days of Gran Turismo 4 using a D pad, however experience with a yum cha brand wheel completely killed Mac Dude’s budding career. Such controllers are the work of the devil.<br /><br />Recently Mac Dude’s latent racing itch awoke through lurking in the atomic F1 thread and a spate of speeding tickets. The deal was sealed by Lambo’s donation of his training wheel and the rest is history. Mac Dude is using the winter 2011 season to get ready for 2011, if you know what I mean. Getting the right racing position, car setup, learning how to choose tyres and the purpose of visiting the pits aside from the mandatory mid-race twinkle (the g-forces play havoc with his bladder).<br /><br />Current goals are modest – start a race from any other position on the grid other than last and to actually finish a fuckin race.<br /><br />A journey of a thousand miles begins with a single step.<br /><br />Vroom Vroom…</p>]]></bodyText>
