        <summary><![CDATA[Now a consistently fast driver, roxas3sora3 is expected to challenge for the occasional podium position this season.  After appearing irregularly in previous seasons, Williams have got themselves a strong driver pairing with inclusion of sora in their team.  Widely regarded as Fredzfrogs nemisis he is sure to ignite races and thrill crowds as he battles for mid-field supremacy and the right to be #1 driver in his team.]]></summary>
        <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>The passion for roxas3sora3 started at a young age at 5 when he laid eyes on the Mazda 737B winning Le Mans on a small CRT TV in the lounge room. Swearing he'll get into motorsport some day, that dream was crushed at the lack of enthusiasm by his parents. Although there were many distractions between that elusive dream and as well as other factors such as new FPS games, it took until Gran Turismo 4 and as well as the purchase of the Logitech Driving Force EX wheel to reignite that passion.</p>
<p>After several seasons competing singularly on the GT circuits and as well as other racing games, it took 2010 before roxas3sora3 got into F1 after earning his stripes on the F1 simulation at Atomic Live. Though he was 7 seconds off the lead, he finally broke through on F1 2010 being a lead driver for Virgin Racing. It wasn't long before he made his presence felt at the second season with a third place podium. However, inconsistent family moments and as well as thoughts over his future stemmed his pace for season three. In the rare participation occasions, he has shown much improvement in qualifying but albeit slower race pace.</p>
<p>He'll be looking forward to the new season given it is a new slate for all competitors.</p>]]></bodyText>
