      <Team id="1607" parentID="1090" level="3" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1195" template="1196" sortOrder="5" createDate="2011-08-16T15:29:36" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:08" nodeName="McLaren" urlName="mclaren" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1090,1607" isDoc="">
        <teamId>1</teamId>
        <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Throughout the history of the Atomic F1 champsionship McLaren have unexpectedly enjoyed only moderate success.  Their season 1 pairing of TurrbalTerror and bobaj0r failed to net either title.  It wasn't until Flouncy arrived on the scene with a fast teammate in Eradicator84 that they managed championship success, taking out the Drivers title.  Season 3 saw a return to the familiar lineup of TurrbalTerror and bobaj0r, which while they managed to secure a victory and a few pole positions, they placed below their own expectations in both title chases.</p>
<p>The woking based team have again signed TurrbalTerror and bobaj0r for Season 4.  Thanks to the teamming rules introduced in this season, McLaren are expected to dominate the constructors title this year, with two very fast, yet inconsistent drivers.  If both drivers can make every event and keep it on track, it will take an act of God to stop McLaren.</p>]]></bodyText>
