              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Despite his move to Red Bull Racing there seems to be no list of companies willing to line up behind F1 driver Krispy.  Atomic F1 today confirmed that Krispy will now feature the famous brand on the livery of the RB6 for the rest of the season.  <br /> <br /> A spokes model for Libra had this to say, "we are thrilled to be onboard with Krispy for the rest of the season and hope to be able to provide with him all the comfort and protection he needs, and with as many wings as necessary to stay dry and fresh."</p>]]></content>
              <tags><![CDATA[]]></tags>
            </umbBlogPost>
            <umbBlogPost id="1148" parentID="1147" level="6" writerID="0" creatorID="1" nodeType="1053" template="1046" sortOrder="2" createDate="2011-05-06T08:01:28" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:09" nodeName="Ghost reveals reason for move to Williams" urlName="ghost-reveals-reason-for-move-to-williams" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Lambo" path="-1,1084,1057,1145,1146,1147,1148" isDoc="">
              <closeComments>0</closeComments>
              <PostDate>2010-10-19T00:00:00</PostDate>
              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>In a not so surprising development, it's been revealed that former Lotus driver Ghost was kicked out for indiscretions at their annual team meeting. "The truth of the matter was that I was kicked out of Lotus after being caught naked and drunk on the roof of the hotel with hookers and cocaine.  But as that was all an internal matter, no other team knew about it and I was snatched up by Williams."  Mike Gascoyne says that it is unfortunate that Ghost had to leave. "I wish him good luck in Williams and hope he'll have a fun time with them." It is unknown why Williams wanted Ghost after this incident, however reports have confirmed the departing of Krispy to Red Bull.  Frank Williams has confirmed that the lack of pace shown by Krispy was the reason for his departure to Red Bull.  "In the interest of the team, Krispy departed because of a lack of results.  I do believe he wanted a team mate to support and so I support his decision to move."</p>]]></content>
              <tags><![CDATA[]]></tags>
            </umbBlogPost>
            <umbBlogPost id="1149" parentID="1147" level="6" writerID="0" creatorID="1" nodeType="1053" template="1046" sortOrder="3" createDate="2011-05-06T08:02:54" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:09" nodeName="Virgin Racing remain optimistic" urlName="virgin-racing-remain-optimistic" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Lambo" path="-1,1084,1057,1145,1146,1147,1149" isDoc="">
              <closeComments>0</closeComments>
              <PostDate>2010-10-19T00:00:00</PostDate>
              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Virgin racing team principal John Booth shrugged aside rumours that Virgin Racing may bow out of the competition. "At the moment, we're doing the best we can given the circumstances of joining this late and not having tested the car as much we'd like . Roxas3sora3 has given us some solid results given that we've been expecting to be at the back of the field. Roxas3sora3 managed to put us into 8th and 6th respective. Hopefully for the next few rounds, we can pick up the pace and translate it into decent lap times." roxas3sora3 shares the same sentiment. "The problem is that I'm just new to the scene and to be honest, my lap times are reflecting that issue. I'm not a wonder machine that the other drivers are. Hopefully for next round, it can be translated better than 8th or 6th."</p>]]></content>
              <tags><![CDATA[]]></tags>
