              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Mclarens early season form was marred by inconsistency and reliability issues, however team boss Martin Whitmarsh believes that his team has now solved those issues and is looking forward to challenging the front runners Force India again.  "We discovered a flaw in our car design that was impacting performance and reliability and I apologise to Kikz especially that this wasn't discovered earlier."  When asked what the issue was Whitmarsh revealed that a faulty automatic garage door was to blame. "We discovered a fault in Kikz's garage door mechanism and we believe this is the source of our troubles in the MP4-25."  When asked if using such a device as opposed to other teams like Force India who opted for slower but more reliable manual roller doors was a mistake Whitmarsh assured fans  "Certainly not, the performance benefit far out ways the negatives of using such a system." <br /> <br /> While automatic doors won't be banned next season, the Formula One Teams Association has unanimously voted to not use the technology in 2011.</p>]]></content>
