              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Current Willams driver Mark84 has been rumoured to be considering making the switching from Formula One to Super Mario Kart at the end of the 2010 Atomic F1 season. Inside sources within the paddock report that Mark84 has been un-happy at Williams and is considering leaving the sport to pursue the possibility of driving in the lucrative Japanese series. Mark84’s manager Koopa Troopa could neither confirm nor deny the rumours. “Mark84 has a contract with Williams till the end of the current season and he intends to honour that contract fully.” Requests for comment from Mark84 directly have been met with silence, however one insider believes if he does make the switch it “will throw the F1 driver market wide open.”  It is not the first time an F1 driver has made the switch, in 1992 Princess Peach after a successful stint at Benetton left to take up a seat in the famous '1Up' Kart Team.</p>]]></content>
