              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>The surprise DNF result from roxas3sora3 was main word across pit lane after the young driver bowed out of contention just one lap into the race. Escaping a chaotic first corner in 4th (up from 8th), roxas3sora3 retired without even finishing the first lap. It was unknown why he had thrown in the towel but reports seems to circulate that the driver was forced to retire due to personal reasons. In a statement today, roxas3sora3 asked everyone to keep racing and keep him in their thoughts. <br /> <br /> When asked, John Booth shrugged his shoulders. "This is a personal moment for roxas3sora3. As a team, we're just as shocked as he is for that decision. If it came down to me, I would have done the same. No man would make such a decision lightly without bearing the cost of that. He's a strong and passionate driver. Hopefully, the next few races will get the man back."<br /> <br /> The race was marked with drama throughout qualifying with bushipoo hitting the barrier hard in the last few minutes of qualifying. During the first lap, the track caught out several drivers, with the first 3 and roxas3sora3 escaping the carnage. After the retirement of roxas3sora3, the race remained incident free apart from several wings being lost and punctures which costed several drivers. With the weekend over, it remains to see whether or not roxas3sora3 can bounce back from the painful finish he had to endure.</p>]]></content>
