              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>McLaren team boss Martin Whitmarsh is refusing to give up on his teams chances of winning the constructors championship despite now being more than 60 points behind with only two races left.  "We can still do it.  We have some updates coming up that will give us an edge in the next two races which we think will close the gap to Force India."  When asked how that can be considering the points gap with only two races left, Whitmarsh explained "we won't give up till it's mathematically impossible."  Driver bobaj0r felt that the team were close but not close enough.  "For sure the performance is there, and if we had say seven or eight more races without Force India, I think we could certainly win."  Force India's Vijay Mallya dismissed Whitmarsh's comments as 'retarded'.</p>
<p>With only two races remaining the battle for second is very much between Williams and Mclaren with only 18 points separating them.</p>]]></content>
