              <teaser><![CDATA[atomicf1.com has been refreshed for Season #3.  Now with computerised stastics and more to come.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>To celebrate the start of Season #3 of the atomic F1 competition, the site has been refreshed inside-out.  We're now running on Umbraco CMS and the statistics engine is database driven. </p>
<p><strong>What does this mean?</strong><br /> Mainly it means no more long hours of calculating gigabytes of stats for circuits, teams, drivers, and seasons in interesting formats.  We've fired up all 8 cyclinders, opened the DRS and drained the KERS dry to get maximum performance.  With calculations being handled by machine, we can focus on the cool and interesting naratives behind the stars of the Atomic F1 competition.</p>
<p><strong>Is there more too come?</strong><br /> You better believe it! While we've got the data model humming alone, ninja's that we are, we still couldn't get the front end complete in time for season launch.  Coming in the next few weeks are</p>
<ul>
<li>Driver Statistics, covering number of races competed, points scored, wins, poles, and more.</li>
<li>Team Statistics, mirroring driver stats</li>
<li>Circuit records and previous race holders.</li>
</ul>
<p>We're also working on getting more video and other media content up.  And we've gone social - on twitter @atomicf1.</p>]]></content>
