              <teaser><![CDATA[With the chequered flag now falling on the final race and the seasong coming to a close, we recap the last 19 rounds and announce the winners of the first annual Atomic F1 awards voted by the drivers themselves.  Our resident Atomic F1 expert Jonathan Legard reports.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>With the chequered flag now falling on the final race and the seasong coming to a close, we recap the last 19 rounds and announce the winners of the first annual Atomic F1 awards voted by the drivers themselves.  Our resident Atomic F1 expert Jonathan Legard reports.<br /> <br /> Going into the season opener in Bahrain there was high expectations from within the Atomic F1 paddock.  There was pressure and expectation on alot of drivers, but perhaps no more so then on Flouncy.  Some would argue that with better reliability the fight with Lambo might have been closer last season, but alas it wasn't to be.  We look now at how season two unfolded.<br /> <br /> The Bahrain opener would be a clear indication of Flouncy's intentions comfortably taking pole by 4 tenths over Lambo, and controlling the race from start to finish, leading last years team mate Lambo over the line with a comfortable 36 second gap.  Lambo's new team mate Kikz would round out the top three, giving Force India the first double podium finish of the season.<br /> <br /> Qualifying in Australia was marred with bad weather, with rain interrupting the qualifying.  As it started to dry out times started to tumble with Lambo taking the last possible opportunity to bolt on intermediate tires and set a quick lap securing maiden pole of the season by one tenth.  However it was not to be with the tricky conditions causing problems for most drivers, it would be Ghost who would prove to be untouchable in the wet and post his sixth carer victory for Lotus Racing.  Flouncy and Lambo rounding off the podium.<br /> <br /> Round three the competition headed to Sepang where it's mixture of tight twisty low speed corners and two long straights making overpassing possible.  Weather would always play a part here and qualifying was no different with rain affecting proceedings.  Flouncy was able to find a good balance clocking a best time some 1.2 seconds quicker than the Force India of Kikz and register his second pole position of the year.  Race day would prove to be dry and the finishing order of qualifying didn't change throughout the race.  Mansill leading home Kikz with the Lotus of Ghost rounding out the podium.<br /> <br /> The Atomic F1 circus headed to China for the fourth round of the championship where Lotus driver Ghost would cement his title of 'wet weather specialist' with a stunning win in wet from third on the grid.  Qualifying would be dry affair and once again Flouncy would prove that his domination of the fly away races would continue with a huge 7 tenths gap to second place Mark in the sister McLaren followed by the Lotus of Ghost.  However rain is the great equalizer in F1 and Ghost would prove supreme in the testing conditions registering his second win of the season and cementing himself as a true title contender.<br /> <br /> Catalunya would be the first of the European races where Force India's Lambo hoped would prove to be the turning point in his championship charge.  Qualifying was dry and it proved to be very competitive with the top 4 drivers separate by less than 6 tenths of a second.  The fight came down to Force India's Lambo and McLarens Flouncy with the final margin less than 6 one hundredths of a second with Lambo nudging out his second pole of the season.  The Lotus of Ghost and the second Force India of Kikz would round out the top four.  Race day would be largely uneventful with a good controlled win by Lambo leading home Flouncy with Ghost rounding out the podium.  The top 4 cars however being only separated by 35 seconds in the end.<br /> <br /> Monaco would prove to be the turning point in the championship battle for Lambo.  Torro Rossos Fredzfrog would steal all the headlines destroying his car on the first lap of qualifying forcing his garage into a long night as they put the car back together for the race.  Having secured his 3rd pole position on the historic street circuit by an incredible 1.4 seconds external factors would see that front row change to the second row with a 3rd place start.  It would prove to be a catalyst for a first corner tangle with the Torro Rosso of Fredzfrog.  Struggling with front end damage a good recovery drive would see him secure second, but not before the McLaren of Flouncy taking a comfortable victory.  Flouncy taking home his 3rd win of the season.<br /> <br /> Round 7 at Istanbul would prove to be the closest pole shootout of the season with all 5 top drivers within 8 tenths of each other.  Once again a strong qualifying result from Lambo taking his 3rd consecutive pole over Ghost by half a second with Flouncy and Kikz rounding out the top 4.  However a horror race start and poor pace would prove to be fatal and Flouncy would cruise to victory recording his 2nd consecutive win, and 4th win of the season.  A solid drive from Ghost would see a well deserved podium as well as pole sitter Lambo rounding out the podium in 3rd.<br /> <br /> It would be a make or break Canadian Grand Prix for Force India as Lambo recorded his 4th consecutive pole position but so far only being able to convert one of those into race victory so far this season.  The Force India was exceptionally strong around the Gilles Velleneuve circuit with both cars on the front row of the grid with the Lotus of Ghost and McLaren of Flouncy rounding out the top 2 rows.  A solid start by the front grid would see the first 5 laps fairly uneventful, however lap 6 would see a spin by Lambo resulting in what would look like another wasted opportunity, however solid race pace and good pit stop would see Lambo cruise to his 2nd victory of the season and the 2nd 1-2 finish for Force India with Flouncy rounding out the podium.  A solid 4th from the Lotus of Ghost following home the second of the McLarens of Mark.<br /> <br /> The run of pole positions for Lambo would come to a close as Ghost would post Lotus Racings first pole position of the season with a dominate display in Valencia pipping the McLaren of Flouncy by 6 tenths.  Force India's Lambo and Kikz would round out the send row.  A good half a second and second off the pace of Ghost.  However as it has in the past wet weather would play a crucial role.  The race would begin wet and a stunning start from Lambo would see him catapult up to first on the first corner as the tricky conditions caused both the Lotus of Ghost and the McLaren of Flouncy to run wide into the first turn.  However you can never discount Ghost in the wet and a mistake by Lambo on lap 8 would have the two drivers running neck and neck.  As the rain eased the slicks were clearly the way to go as Lambo would pit on lap 9 switching to the option tire, which in itself was a gamble with quite a few laps to go having to make them last.  Flouncy switched to the prime tire which would definitely last the race distance, but would be slower during it's first few laps.  However the gamble payed off with Lambo bringing home the Force India in front of the fast finishing Flouncy.  Lambo racking up his 3rd victory of the season and his second consecutive race win.  Ghost's Lotus and Force India's Kikz would round out the top 4.<br /> <br /> Tricky conditions would meet drivers for qualifying for the British Grand Prix with wet weather once again proving to be difficult to pin a good lap.  Again choosing the right tire at the right time proved critical as once again Lambo would put the Force India on pole switching to option tires for a last final lap and getting pole by half a second over team mate Kikz with Ghost once again proving his might in wet weather putting the Lotus ahead of McLaren's Flouncy.  A good start and some close racing would see the top 3 switch places a number of times in the first 9 laps.  Lap 10 would see all the top 3 come into the pits, clearly tho Lambo couldn't find a good rhythm on the hard tires and struggled for race pace as Mark made a stunning pass into turn one to steal 4th.  Silverstone would prove to be another favourite as Flouncy posted his 5th race victory and cement his place at the top of the championship table. Ghost once again proving consistency is just as important as sheer pace placed second with Force India's Kikz rounding out the podium.<br /> <br /> Germany would prove to be a close qualifying tussle between Lotus's Ghost, Force India's Lambo and McLarens Flouncy.  Less than 2 tenths would separate the trio on the qualifying run.  Ghost making the most of his options pipping Lambo and Flouncy to pole.  Controversy would strike on the tight high speed section of turn 9 as Flouncy attempted a pass on Lambo, neither driver yielding and contact was made, causing damage to the front wing of Lambo.  The ensuing damage forcing an early pit stop for the primes.  Ghost in the mean time had pulled a comfortable gap and was able to cruise to victory leading home Flouncy and Force India's Lambo.  It was Ghost's third win of the season equalling Lambo's efforts, but still trailing behind McLaren's Flouncy with 5 wins.<br /> <br /> With the controversy of Germany still running hot, F1 moved to the Hungaroring in Budapest for round 12.  Close qualifying again sees Flouncy on pole by 2 tenths ahead of rival Lambo and Mark close behind.  A flying start by Mark would see him overtake Lambo into turn one, however running wide out of the same turn Flouncy's McLaren rejoining the track made contact dropping his team mate back and allowing Lambo's Force India to to regain 2nd place.  The ensuring battle over the next few laps would see the lead switch a number of times between the ex team mates pitted eventually on lap 9 as both pitted, a quicker pit stop by the McLaren garage saw the Force India come out 2nd.  However it would not be the end of the problems for the Force India driver as he was forced to pit again a few laps later with a front puncture losing out another place to Mark.  The ensuing battle as Lambo on his fresher tires was able to steal 3rd place, while up the front Flouncy cruised to this 6th race win of the year equalling the number of wins Lambo had when he took out the championship.  Once again a sold race from Ghost holding onto second and keep Flouncy honest just 13 seconds down the road.<br /> <br /> If there are two things that go hand in hand for Spa it's rain and more rain.  And qualifying was no different as the rain yet again provided a challenge to the drivers.  In trying conditions it would be Force India's Kikz who would outshine team mate Lambo to pip him to pole by 2 tenths.  Flouncy and Ghost rounding out the 2nd row.  Eyes clearly on Ghost who as from previous races fancied his chances in the rain.  A first corner incident with Lambo and Torro Rosso's fredzfrog would see the Force India drop to the back of the field, however in perhaps his finest drive of the season Lambo would make his way through the field with the highlight a solid pass on Flouncy into campus corner.  Chasing down Ghost who at this stage had build up a large lead Lambo made a pass on a drying track to take the lead.  With a track that was clearly ready for slicks Lambo pitted from the lead letting Ghost back through choosing to keep going on his wets despite his pitwall requesting he come in.  With his wets completely destroyed Lambo was able to take the lead back with several laps to go.  McLaren's Flouncy having also stopped for slicks was now chasing down 2nd place Ghost who on very worn tires was lapping very slowly and eventually unable to hold off as Flouncy crossed the line ahead of Ghost.  Lambo posted his 4th win of the season and kept the possibility of a championship alive.<br /> <br /> It was clear now leading into Round 14 of the season that two title contenders where fighting it out.  Last years champion Force India's Lambo and his ex team mate McLaren's Flouncy would battle it out again for pole.  Lambo's strong qualifying this year would continue beating Flouncy by just 2 one hundredths of a second.  The second McLaren of Mark would put his car just ahead of Lotus's Ghost filling out the top two grids.  A solid race start would see a drag race into turn one as Lambo missed the breaking zone and had to take the short cut into turn one.  On lap 3 breaking into the same corner the Force India driver dropped one to many gears and spun leaving the Flouncy's McLaren to take the lead.  However shortly two laps later the McLaren drifted onto the grass out of the second lesmo and the nearly collided with the Force India coming through.  After that incident it was a relatively straight forward race with Lambo taking the comfortable victory posting his 5th victory, and second consecutive race win.  Lotus would score yet another podium with Ghost crossing the line in 3rd and McLaren's Mark rounding out the top 4.<br /> <br /> Round 15 would see us almost cement Flouncy's first championship with a measured and controlled drive by the McLaren driver.  Lambo would again rue misfortune having yet again put his Force India on pole but not be able to follow up with a win.  Flouncy would be beaten to pole by half a second, but like all street circuits keeping it out of the wall would prove to be a challenge.  Turn one would once again prove chaotic with Flouncy sneaking up the inside of turn one pushing Lambo slightly wide, giving the sister McLaren of Mark an opportunity to go through as well.  However a tap from behind would see the Force India forced to the back of the field.  From then on it was a controlled race with Flouncy recording his 7th win of the season to set a new record for wins in a season.  Lotus's Ghost once again proved consistent having recovered from down the field after the first corner incident to claim second.  The second McLaren of Mark would round out the podium.With all but the glimmer of hope of retaining the championship, Lambo would need an almost DNF from Flouncy to have any hope of going back to back, and clearly Japan was not going to be an easy task.  McLaren's Flouncy was sublime posting a pole position time that was nearly 2 seconds faster than second place Kikz in the Forice India.  The second McLaren of Mark would pip the Lotus of Ghost by only 3 tenths to round out the top four.  With such a domination of qualifying it was clear Flouncy was the driver to beat, but no one did and Flouncy claimed his 8th win, as well as his first championship title.  Team mate Mark would round out a 1-2 finish for the team with Virgin Racing's Sora scoring the teams first podium, as well as his best finish to date.<br /> <br /> With the championship over it was only about pride now, and it was clear that perhaps with the pressure of the title now off McLaren's Flouncy could relax as the pole shootout was clearly a battle between Flouncy's team mate Mark and Force India's Lambo.  With only 2 minutes remaining Mark had the better of Lambo beating him pole by only 3 tenths.  Ghost and Flouncy would round out the top 4.  A shocking start by Lambo off the line saw both Flouncy and the Virgin of Sora get past on the opening corner.  Lambo was lucky not to lose a front wing as the Virgin nearly lost it out of turn two.  However as both Sora and Flouncy overshot turn 3 Lambo was able to make his way past Flouncy.  Within the same lap a great move on the outside of turn 7 gave back the 2nd place lost to the start.  The ensuing battle as the Force India followed the gear box of the McLaren went on for a number of laps before on Lap 9 Mark pitted, leaving the Force India driver to put in a gap to try and come out in front.  A great inlap and pit stop allowed the Force India to come just out in from of the McLaren, however on new cold tires that weren't up to temperature Mark was able to make the pass into turn 3.  For the next several laps the Force India looked for ways to pass but it wasn't until a mistake into turn 7 cost Mark not only the lead but also second place as the Lotus of Ghost passed as well.  It should have been a cruise to victory as Lambo maintained a solid gap to second place Ghost.  But a critical error on lap 21 saw that lead cut to nothing as Ghost was all over the back of the Force India.  Into the final last turns a small tap from behind shot Lambo wide and gave Ghost the chance to pass, crossing the line only 3 tenths in front of Lambo.  Lambo rueing the mistake and Ghost ecstatic over his 3rd victory of the year.  Mark despite his error only 15 seconds behind rounding out the podium.  It would also mark the end of an incredible 16 consecutive podiums for Flouncy.<br /> <br /> The second final in Brazil while irrelevant in the title battle would see yet again one of the closest qualifying sessions ever with the top 5 drivers separated by 7 tenths only.  It would by McLaren's Flouncy beating the Lotus of Ghost to pole, with Mark and Lambo rounding out the top 4.  Most notable improvement front the back field team of Torro Rosso as Fredzfrog put his car within 2 seconds of the lead time.  The weather would play a big part as heavy rain met the drivers for the start of the race.  Almost all drivers went off at some stage and it seemed a case of survival rather than sheer speed.  The track did dry with a few laps remaining but too little too late as Flouncy would go on to record his 9th and final win of the year.  Ghost once again proving that he's a master in wet conditions, and a solid race from Mark in the sister McLaren rounded out the top 3.<br /> <br /> The final round in Abu Dhabi saw the first 75% race, and considering that's 41 laps would prove physically the toughest race of the year on drivers.  The Force India drivers were very quick around the 5.5KM circuit with Lambo pipping team mate Kikz by only 3 tenths.  McLaren's Mark a further half a second behind Kikz with Ghost rounding out the front two grids.  A clean start by both the Force India's saw close racing.  While team orders would have been clearly to give each other space, both raced each other hard.  Lambo was the first to pit on lap 13 with Kikz hoping to leapfrog him pitting one lap later, however a steering issue forced the Force India to call of any hopes of a decent result.  The rest of the race turning into a testing session.  From then on it was a controlled race till the end, but even so the Force India clearly very fast around the track winning by a massive 57 seconds.  Lambo would claim his 6th win of the year, but would rue a number of races and chances of beating rival Flouncy.<br /> <br /> <strong>Championship Standings:</strong><br /> Flouncy 466<br /> Lambo 411<br /> Ghost 383<em><strong><br /> </strong></em></p>]]></content>
