              <teaser><![CDATA[Now the season is done, our expert panel has voted and here are the results.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><strong>Most improved driver</strong> - Ghost<br /> A close battle with both Fredzfrog and Ghost, it would be the stunning drives in the wet and his 4 race victories that would nudge him ahead of the vastly improved frog.<br /> Give him the right team and Ghost could well be fighting for a championship next season.<br /> <br /> <strong>Personality of the season</strong> - Fredfrog<br /> There are few people who can plow into a wall at 66G's so spectacularly and frequently as Fredzfrog.  Unanimous in result, the Torro Rosso driver was easily the most entertaining driver of the year.  Fast on the improvement however we can see big things in Season 3.<br /> <br /> <strong>Best qualifier of the season</strong> - Lambo<br /> Perhaps the Mark Webber of qualifying, Lambo put his Force India on pole 9 times this season, however of those 9, only 4 were converted into race victories.  With better luck more would be expected next season.<br /> <br /> <strong>Drive of the season</strong> - Ghost<br /> In perhaps his finest drive of the season Lotus driver Ghost proved that he is up there with the masters when it comes to handling wet weather.  Punching above his weight in Melbourne he drove a flawless race to record his 4th carer victory in difficult conditions.  One to watch for in season 3.<br /> <br /> <strong>Best team of the season</strong> - Lotus<br /> This one was always going to be close, but many didn't expect this result.  While it has to be said the constructors champions would always be in the mix, the small one man outfit at Lotus showed us what really being in a team of one was all about.  There's no question that given the right team mate Ghost will be tough to beat.<br /> <br /> <strong>Best race of the season</strong> - British Grand Prix<br /> A pivotal round that had everything going, mixed weather, close racing and exciting finish.  A race that was extremely close and exciting to witness.<br /> <br /> <strong>Worst race of the season</strong> - Monaco Grand Prix<br /> It would seem that putting a wall right next to the racing track is a bad idea, and it appears most drivers agree.  Despite it's heritage and sentimentality Monaco has been voted by the drivers as the worst GP of the season.  This seasons race was highlighted with a DNF in qualifying, a number of lost front wings and an exorbitant number of pits.  Perhaps season 3 will result in a happier ending.<br /> <br /> <strong>Best driver of the season</strong> - Flouncy<br /> I don't think there was much doubt on who was the best all rounder this season.  Consistency and speed taking 9 wins, and 16 podiums on the way to his first championship.  Dominated the fly away races with 2 wins and 2 2nd's it took till round 8 just to score a 3rd place.  With a worst result of 4th at round 17 at Korea perhaps we have seen the highest score by a driver.  Time will tell.  Perhaps the Vettel of our time once he's at the front he generally stays there with perhaps the best pole to win conversion so far.  Will there be more glory to come?</p>]]></content>
