              <teaser><![CDATA[Who's who in the zoo of AtomicF1 and how are they shaping up for the new season?]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/392/21_f109_Make_Cars_Green_Tyres_02_350x234.jpg"  width="350"  height="234" alt="21_f109_Make_Cars_Green_Tyres_02.jpg" style="float: right;"/></p>
<p><strong>Flouncy - Red Bull</strong><br /> Speed and track affinity, plus improved consistency and overall race pace along with ongoing qualifying capacity puts the Flounce high on bookies lists.</p>
<p><br /> <strong>Ghost - Lotus</strong><br /> Through season 2 Ghost 'kept the bastards honest', always threatening and, on increasing occasion, taking the big points. Could season 3 be his championship season?<br /> <br /> The man is highly rated in traffic, rarely makes errors and possesses a relentless head of steam that never gives anyone ahead of him a chance to relax.<br /> <br /> Ghost can sit on your tail for a dozen laps, if you're in peak form that is. Otherwise any weakness he senses is soon pounced upon. Given the chance he's past and away.<br /> <br /> Ghost is the god king of wet weather racing.<br /> <br /> <strong>Lambo - Renault</strong><br /> Fusing highly refined technical skills with pile-driving race pace, Lambo rarely, if ever, makes a mistake when in clean air. On rare occasion prone to<br /> pressure from behind, Lambo nevertheless is expected to put in a supreme performance in the season 3 season and is determined to push for his second championship.<br /> <br /> Poor starts in some season 2 races were costly, though Lambo is able to come back from situations that would sink other drivers.<br /> <br /> <strong>Fredzfrog - Torro Rosso</strong><br /> After putting in some solid performances in season 2, showing real growth and impressing with occasionally blistering qualifying speed, the fredz is expected to run highly in the upper half of the grid in this, his graduation year.<br /> <br /> <strong>Kikz - McLaren</strong><br /> Responsibilities as the manager of his own family F1 team, as well as wavering commitment to the iRacing series has prevented kikz from showing the commitment to make him a contender in season 2.<br /> <br /> When he does get his focus on, kikz can be a devestatingly fast driver, putting in qualifying lap pace in a race, though not usually during actual qualifying. Consistency has been his big question mark in the past.<br /> <br /> With old pal bobaj0r back on the track kikz is expected to show renewed passion for F1 and is expected to appear frequently on the podiium.<br /> <br /> <strong>bobaj0r - Ferrari</strong><br /> Fast straight out of the box in season 1, bobaj0r mysteriously disappeared during season 2.<br /> <br /> Without the benefit of F1 experience that matches other racers, can boba find his mojo quickly and scythe up the field early enough to bank valuable opening round championship points?<br /> <br /> <strong>Bollum</strong><br /> A mid field prospect who could run high or low in the field, depending on how things go.<br /> <br /> <strong>nobody813</strong><br /> This sponsored driver could surprise many with raw natural speed. Mostly it is hoped that first corner etiquette is high on his list of talents.<br /> <br /> <strong>Hulkster - Williams</strong><br /> Out of retirement, the former V8 Supercars force could shock many in the glamour world of F1. Capable of great speed, consistency and trash talk, the Hulks has the coolest team HQ on the field.<br /> <br /> With plenty of race experience, Hulks is expected to soon slot into competitive traffic conditions and display smooth safe driving.<br /> <br /> <strong>MacDude</strong><br /> Another sponsored driver, Mac Dude is a complete unknown but could surprise many. Not expected to rack up early podiums, Mac Dude nevertheless joins a handful of rookies in the Season 3 lineup, putting him in a good position to drive for midfield points.</p>]]></content>
