              <content><![CDATA[<p>After a season on the sidelines Williams F1 announced today they are back with the signing of their newest driver for season 3. Team principal Sir Frank Williams had this to say. "We are exceptionaly proud to announce that hulkster will be leading our championship charge for season 3. He's a raw tallent that I'm sure will grow over the season. And since we are about the same age, we have alot in common." Williams Technical director Sam Michael was upbeat about the teams chances. "I know he's old and smells like an obese mans twosies, but he's also fast and very cheap. We just have to make sure we get him back to the retirement village before 4.30 for bed."</p>
<p><img src="~/media/288/hulkster-wheel_500x318.jpg"  width="500"  height="318" alt="hulkster-wheel" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"/></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Hulkster while inexperinced in F1 did cut his teeth in open wheel racing in his younger years, taking several state and national 'penny farthing open wheel' championships.</p>]]></content>
