              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[The F1 circus returns after the autumn break.  Have the lagging teams made up ground?  Will McLaren close the gap to the two top teams, or will Group Force India and their superstars continue to runaway?]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/762/73170845_400x267.jpg"  width="400"  height="267" alt="f1 tyres" style="float: right;"/></p>
<p>The return to racing after the Autumn break is nearly upon us.  This weekend sees the circus move north to the Asia double, Malaysia and China.</p>
<p>In Season 2 World Champion Flouncy set a blistering qualifying pace to sit comfortably on pole from TurrbalTerror, with a Vettel-esque 1.2 seconds over the feild.  Flouncy led from start to finish, completely unchallenged, while the rest of the pack slugged it out for the other podium slots.  </p>
<p>If testing pace is anything to go by, this seasons race is looking much more competitive, with TurrbalTerror setting a time in practice the Mclaren team reports as 'a significant amount' faster than last years pole time of 1:36.264.  How much time did the other teams find is the unknown and with times tumbling season after season, even a significant improvement may not be enough to get pole.  If anyone is likely to do it this year it's TurrbalTerror, the current top qualifier for Season 3.</p>
<p>HRT also promises massive speed increases and it's expected Hulks will make his belated F1 debut, after missing the opening two rounds through illness.  MacDude's HRT is reported to sport an updated steering mechanism bringing the HRT into line with the other cars on the grid and hopefully both improve MacDudes own performances and save the runoff areas from excessive wear.</p>
<p>Malaysia is shaping to be an exciting race with an expectedly close battle between Flouncy and HolyGhost79 for the race win.  In following with events in the opening races, TurrbalTerror will sit on pole and be nudged off the track by Flouncy in the opening laps, to eventually finish forth.  The unknown element is the evergreen Atomic Lambo.  Will he turn around his Season 2 form and be a race win challenger or will he struggle to match the two fastest men this season.  </p>
<p>Whatever happens it will be exciting.</p>]]></content>
