              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><strong>Which real world F1 driver inspires you most: Juan Pablo Montoya, Michael Andretti or Luca Badoer, and why?</strong><br />While I respect Montoya for his amazing tennis ability, I draw my inspiration from Luca Badoer.  In Luca we have a driver who is a perennial under achiever.  When he finally got his shot at a Ferrari race drive, some 100 years after his F1 debut he qualified so far off the pace it embarrassed even the slowest cars on the grid.  Yet he didn't give up.  He kept trying to race and continue to go round.  It's that self belief, flying in the face of reality that gives me hope that one day I may become world champion.  I salute you Luca.<br /><br /><strong>Turn 1 presents tremendous challenges to novice drivers, what safety tips can you give these noobs to help prevent ruinous disasters?</strong><br />Pay Flouncy off so he won't hit you.<br /><br /><strong>When starting a race, do you have a plan?</strong><br />I belive the best drivers don't need a plan.  They can rely on instinct, feel, and a bit of magic.  My race engineers and I usually work through Saturday night at each race, comging up with a plan whereby I can position my car in the way of any fast approaching cars come turn 1.<br /><br /><strong>If a cute, happy and innocent small child asks for an autograph straight after a race do you:</strong><br />A. Tell him to fuck off<br />B. Ask him if he's a qualified gearbox engineer, and if not, why is he in your face?<br />--&gt;C. Look for his Mum and rate her.&lt;---<br /><br /><strong>How do you balance disappointing your fans with dissapointing your sponsors?</strong><br /><strong>I have fans?</strong><br />Post-race, when you're finally alone in your elite F1 superstar trailer do you:<br />A. Beat off furiously in anger<br />B. Smack your bitch, then beat off furiously<br />--&gt;C. Lay some pipe with the fan milfs&lt;--<br />D. Call eddie Irvine and agree with everything he says<br />E. Present your lawyers with fresh opportunities for litigation<br /><br /><strong>Evergreen Lambo claims 'victim of circumstance' after a race and blames you for some dumb shit, your response is to:</strong><br />A. Head down and get on with the next race.<br />--&gt;B: A bit of elbow to face diplomacy<br />--&gt;C: Blame Flouncy<br />--&gt;D: Take the cunt out on turn 1 next race<br /><br /><strong>A member of an opposing team has been given the opportunity to interview you and wrecks it by casting nasty aspersions about your track talents. Do you:</strong><br />--&gt;A. Take him out at turn 1 next race <br />B: Ignore him cos he's a dick<br />C: Prove them all wrong by winning<br /><br /><strong>What's your favorite track and why?</strong><br />A drag stip.  Less chance for Flouncy to punt me off.<br /><br /><strong>What tracks do you hate and why?</strong><br />Tracks with corners.  More chance for Flouncy to punt me off.</p>]]></content>
