              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/1150/dodgemcars_400x268.jpg"  width="400"  height="268" alt="dodgemcars" style="float: right;"/></p>
<p>The Season 3 Spainish atomic F1 GP at Catalunya in the beautiful city of Barcelona is looking like a one horse race.  Season 2 race winner Atomic Lambo will be out to recapture some of the form that won him the Season 1 world champsionship and there few better circuits than Barcelona for him to do this. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Catalunya is a super smooth track that works brilliantly with a finely tuned aero-kit, as is on board the Force India.  The smooth driving style of Lambo should see him capture pole position and drive a consistently fast race to take the flag.  Atomic Lambo isn’t the only driver in the race though and current points leader HolyGhost79 will be out to take yet another win and consolidate his lead in the championship.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Atomicf1 interviewed Season 1 winner and Mclaren driver TurrbalTerror to get his thoughts on the upcoming race.  “If Lambo thinks he’s going to have it all his way, he’s got it all wrong.  The boys at the McLaren factory have been working day and night to build me a car that will withstand the rigours of a high impact Flouncy hit.  With a stronger tub and my  recent practice times, I’m gunning for my first race win of the season” said the much underrated driver.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>The battle for Season 3 championship honours intensifies with a close points table and the probable appearance of a new HRT driver, Hulkster, now that teams funding has been stabilised.  McLaren also expect bobaj0r to come back from his pre-season tennis injury to help take points from the other non-McLaren drivers.</p>]]></content>
