              <content><![CDATA[<p>atomicf1.com interviewed the two atomicf1 world champions, Flouncy and Atomic Lambo, on their thoughts and chances in the upcoming race this weekend.</p>
<p><strong>Flouncy</strong></p>
<p>Catalunya: </p>
<p>For sure, Spain is a track that can give you position as quickly as it takes it away. There are many legitimate and exciting overtaking opportunities coming from every chance -- whether out-braking going into a corner, through the fast corners themselves, and out of them if exit speed is good.</p>
<p>It's as much a technical track as it is one that rewards hot 'seat of pants' aggro driving. I love the dive into the swooping, sweeping turn 1, incredibly exciting stuff.</p>
<p>Catalunya can reward an unusually varied strategy of setups, with both low and high downforce effective here. This is one track I'd really love to see what setups other drivers are running.</p>
<p>I think the track favours our car so I expect a good podium position, along with my team mate.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Monaco: </p>
<p>After last season's win at Monaco I'm full of beans going in. Lambo and I have a traditional rivalry here going back through the history of the sport. Technically it's his turn this season, but I'll be doing all I can to make it two in a row for myself.</p>
<p>The reality though is that it's a bit of a lottery, especially if it's wet. A spun car -- especially at Massanet -- and especially on lap 1, can dictate the race outcome depending on who is in front and who is behind the jammed car.</p>
<p>Patience, concentration and luck are the keys to Monaco. It's an exhausting race and if you're not in the zone from the green light you're not in the running.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Atomic Lambo</strong></p>
<p>For sure I was strong here last season so for sure I'll be looking to be strong again at Catalyuna. For sure it's always difficult because the Red Bull team for sure will be hard to beat, but for sure I have have high expectations going into the European races. For sure.</p>
<p>Last season was very dissapointing considering the strong pace I had in qualifying and the contact with Fredz into the first corner. But my package is very confident around Monte Carlo circuit. I hope to go one better than season 2.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>So there you have it folks, as predicted these two rounds of the atomicf1 championship are going to be very interesting, as arguably the two finest drivers in the world today duke it out for supremacy at F1's resident test track and the crown jewel of the championship.</p>]]></content>
