              <teaser><![CDATA[Driver quotes from Flouncy, Atomic Lambo, TurrbalTerror]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><strong>Flouncy</strong><br />This track always seems like work, still nice with a cool blend of fast variable throttle corners. You really need to manage the throttle so carefully on several corners here...<br /><br />Had a good start off the line and Lambo right in front of me didn't. I had enough speed on him to be at least side by side turning into turn 1, if not past him, but the cheeky bugger saw this and moved to block me, had to lift off... s'alright, I would have done the same thing.<br /><br />Then it was kikz blazing ahead, ghost, lambo and me. A couple of laps in on turn 1 I was following Lambo and he went a bit wide while my line is to follow the curb in the last part, so in a flash I was inside Lambo - it wasn't an overtaking move, just found myself there in a blink of an eye, I did brake to slow and get behind you safely but you turned back in too quickly and we touched. Sorry about that, wasn't going for a move there...<br /><br />A couple of laps later I tapped kikz, you went invisible right as I was close and I couldn't tell where you were. That hardly happens so unsure why the game decided to do that. In any case I tapped you, so sorry about that.<br /><br />Then it was me and ghosty, I had the lead for a good while and he was enough car lengths behind to give me comfort, but threaten me all the time. I went wide on that bloody second last corner (end of the epic straight - you know, the place that costs you races...) and he was by. I stayed behind for a while til he pulled away a football field length.<br /><br />Last few laps I was safely in 2nd enough to really take risks and push, engine on fast and went all out. Seemed to close a bit but not enough, til last couple of laps all of a sudden I was on him. Not quite enough to challenge, though fredz positioned himself nicely on the second last corner right between us, but alas it didn't help me.</p>
<p><br /><br /><strong>Lambo</strong><br />Shaghai is also a pet hate. Not because it's technical, which it is, has a similar first corner chain that you need to get right to get the best drive out of the second bend, but because it's bumpy. So bumpy. Especially the back straight corner, really hard to get a good setup. Had a decent qualifying lap, but lack of practice this week really hurt me as I did probably 2 or 3 more laps then I would have liked. I had a badish start. Got of the line ok but I knew ben starting in 4th would be behind me on the grid, and If I've learned anything from Singapore...and Korea....and Melbourne....he'll attack the inside. Getting off the line I short shifted 3rd but deliberately parked my car on the very inside to deny Ben the chance of going up the inside (you never got beside me Ben, if you had, youd be in the wall). Kikz had a monster start. While I was busy defending Ben I forgot about him and he navigated around the outside of me, and then the inside of Ghost. Looked very good on the replay. Next lap or so Ben chased me but into the first corner I took a wider line as to have the inside going into the second corner, but had contact with Ben. I havn't seen the replay yet, but it was quite a shunt and sent me spinning. From then on it was a lonely race in 4th. Overall a dissapointing round. While I made mistakes I lost chunks of time to incidents that didn't fell were my fault. But with the fly races done thankfully, we have two tracks comeing up which I do love. Catalyuna and Monaco. Hope to do better at Monaco considering the disspoaintment of last season.</p>
<p><br /><strong>TurrbalTerror</strong><br />China was ok. I had good qualifying speed and could was close. Closer than Sepang anyway. I really enjoy the first few turns and I think I've always done exceptionally well there. I got into first place from the start and led for the first 6-7 laps Ghost start to mount an effort. We battled closely, with me actively defending lines. We had an both had an off on the hairpin after the straight as I took the inside line and he went left. Ghost was probably being polite and not turning in on me. I missed my break point being too concerned with defending and would have certainly hit Ghost if he turned in. I managed to get back on track still in the lead but Flouncy was close behind. He came up in the inside in turn 1 and I got tapped sending me off into the sand to jump a few curbs. Not too bad. I was about 4-5 second back and in 3rd when I got on track. A few laps later Fredzfrog was off on the same turn and as he joined the track he also joined my sidepod. no damage but again an off and a few more seconds lost. I made an error on 6 for 4 consecutive laps near the end, when Bollum was close behind. In the end I cruised into a comfortable 3rd.</p>]]></content>
