              <content><![CDATA[<p>We know whenever we go to Monte Carlo we're going to witness a display of ultimate car control and application of brake and throttle at the hands of Monaco specialist Atomic Lambo.   His laps of Monaco rival the great Ayrton Senna for his ability to find the edge then push past it.  The qualifying time demonstrated this and embarrassed other "fast" drivers, including the current championship leader HolyGhost79.</p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="10" />
<p> </p>
<p>Competitors didn't hold much hope of anything but second place and it was clear from lap one that that was the best they could hope for.</p>
<p>Watch the race highlights below to see what all the fuss is about.</p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Race" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="10" />
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO utubewidth="" utubevideo="Eu9Vi0TXQoM" utubeheight="" macroAlias="uTube.ChromelessPlayer" />
<p> </p>]]></content>
