            <umbBlogPost id="1169" parentID="1173" level="6" writerID="0" creatorID="1" nodeType="1053" template="1046" sortOrder="1" createDate="2011-05-06T08:15:22" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:13" nodeName="Part #3 of our exclusive driver feature series.  Lambo." urlName="part-3-of-our-exclusive-driver-feature-series-lambo" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Lambo" path="-1,1084,1057,1079,1172,1173,1169" isDoc="">
              <closeComments>0</closeComments>
              <PostDate>2011-03-25T00:00:00</PostDate>
              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><strong>1.) How tremendous does it feel to be the only Formula 1 World Champion since Jack Brabham to have built your own car?</strong><br /> I'm kinda shocked to be honest that all it took was some wood, nails and glue.  How hard can it possibly be to build an F1 car?  HRT should give me a call.<br /> <br /> <strong>2.) Who is more inspirational - Ralf Schumacher, Nelson Piquet Jnr or David Coulthard?</strong><br /> Oh it's got to be Nelson Piquet Jnr.  He's shown us that you don't need a spine or balls to be in F1.<br /> <br /><strong> 3.) Describe the Zen technique you use to enter a state of elevated racing consciousness prior to a race.</strong><br /> Kimi passed on a tip to me once that prior to each race you should drop a huge shit.  Not only does it save weight but I've been told that Tibetan Monks cleanse the colon in order to reach new levels of zen and peace.<br /> <br /> <strong>4.) Would you rather be stuck on a desert island with Bernie Ecclestone, Max Mosely or Flavio Briatore? All are drunk and horny.</strong><br /> I've been in a devils threesome with Bernie, and he's just a selfish lover.  At one stage he broke the cardinal rule and made eye contact with me and it's just been weird since then.  Max would want to act out some sort of fantasy 3rd Reich thing, so it's gotta be Flavio.  And with that silky smooth accent who wouldn't.<br /> <br /><strong> 5.) Should Fernando Alonso wear a beard?</strong><br /> I didn't know he was gay?<br /> <br /> <strong>7.) Can you explain Sebastian Vettel's oversized lips and unusual head-shape?</strong><br /> Have you ever seen Justin Beiber and Vettel in the same room?  Me neither.<br /> <br /><strong> 8.) What is your second favourite circuit and why?</strong><br /> Next to Montreal, I do love Monaco.  It rewards the brave and every time I drive it I get flash backs of Senna climbing the hill up to the Massenet corner.<br /> <br /> <strong>9.) What is the secret to Kimi's awesomeness? </strong><br /> The man can teach us so much not just about racing, but life itself.  I mean take a look at this wisdom.  I keep these quotes taped to my toilet door so I while I'm zenning, I can memorize his immortal words.<br /> <br /> "The Constructor’s Championship doesn’t really mean anything to me."<br /> "I’m not interested in what Jackie says. He hasn’t got anything to do with me."<br /> "Coulthard can say what he wants. I’m not interested in what he’s saying."<br /> "I don’t give a damn about what Trulli says."<br /> "Montoya’s comments doesn’t interest me."<br /> "Driving is the only thing I love about F1."<br /> "I’m not interested in what people think about me. I’m not Michael Schumacher."<br /> "Others can sit in the simulators if they want. I'm here to drive."<br /> "Well, in summer there's fishing and fucking. And in winter... the fishing is bad."<br /> <br /> The man is a god.<br /><br /></p>]]></content>
