              <content><![CDATA[<p>Valencia season 3: who will win?</p>
<p> </p>
<p>With the championship tight at the top, the European GP at Valencia is shaping up to be an important point in the championship.  HolyGhost79 has nearly a full race win and pole lead over second place Flouncy, but a poor result here could put him well within reach.  Valencia is a favourite of the current championship leader, so it'll be a tough race.</p>
<p>Here's last seasons qualifying results, to give us an idea of what to expect.</p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="51" />
<p> </p>
<p>With a tightening field we dont' expect such a large spread this year, with it likely the top five drivers will be separated by less than a second. </p>
<p>Will McLaren's steering upgrade prove a boon? or will bobaj0r need a race to come to grips with the changed dynamics.  While on the topic of steering, this weekends Valencia GP should have given Flouncy enough time to optimise his new steering configuration.</p>
<p>Can Lambo take out another win? Will TurrbalTerror keep his recent consistency?  Can Krispy89 get hooked up with the front runners? </p>
<p>This is shaping up to be the biggest GP of the season so far. Be sure not to miss it!</p>]]></content>
