              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>British GP preview<br /><br />One of the iconic grand prix are upon us this weekend, with the race at the airport turned circuit, Silverstone in England for the British grand prix.  Silverstone is a high speed track with a number of challenging corners following the recent redesign.  Getting a car setup to handle both aspects is challenging and getting it right will likely reward the driver with a win or at least a podium position.  Last season saw some of the closest racing in years, as the top four circulated for a numnber of laps, within a few meters of one another before pitstops broke up the show.<br /><br /></p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="52" />
<p><br />Silverstone detester, Atomic Lambo sat on pole position after slippery conditions saw a slightly unexpected grid, with TurrbalTerror in second place.</p>
<p>The race was one by Flouncy, after he drove skillfully through the field.</p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Race" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="52" />
<p> </p>
<p>Bookies for Season 3 would have Flouncy as odds on favourite for pole, with a Group Force India front row lockout. My prediction has bobai0r in third, and Atomic Lambo in fourth, with TurrbalTerror qualifying in fifth position.</p>
<p>This race should see the return of Mac Dude and potentially the first race for Hulkster.  It's going to be a cracker.</p>]]></content>
