            <umbBlogPost id="1346" parentID="1347" level="6" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1053" template="1046" sortOrder="1" createDate="2011-06-10T07:44:33" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:14" nodeName="Season 3 German GP Preview" urlName="season-3-german-gp-preview" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1057,1079,1306,1347,1346" isDoc="">
              <closeComments>0</closeComments>
              <PostDate>2011-06-10T06:44:00</PostDate>
              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>There's no denying that Hockenhiemring is another Atomic Lambo circuit when it comes to raw pace.  He easily sits on top the Super Grid at this track and does well here.  That said, it's not all going to swing Atomic Lambo's way.  Qualifying record holder and current clear championship leader is HolyGhost79, though we hear he may not be able to make this weekends race.</p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="53" />
<p> </p>
<p>Last year's grid was definitely close at the top, with only 0.1s separating the top three qualifiers, in probably the smallest field ever.  </p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Race" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="53" />
<p> </p>
<p>It seems whether or not HolyGhost79 can make this event will determine who the winner will be.  Although this season should be a little more competitive, with bobaj0r and TurrbalTerror both likely competitors up near the front and the addition of ET Rom au and Maverick, along with possibly Mac Dude and Hulkster.</p>
<p>Another exciting race on a track many people enjoy will be the likely result.</p>]]></content>
              <tags><![CDATA[]]></tags>
            </umbBlogPost>
            <umbBlogPost id="1348" parentID="1347" level="6" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1053" template="1046" sortOrder="2" createDate="2011-06-10T13:22:03" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:14" nodeName="Season 3 Hungarian GP Preview" urlName="season-3-hungarian-gp-preview" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1057,1079,1306,1347,1348" isDoc="">
              <closeComments>0</closeComments>
              <PostDate>2011-06-10T13:48:00</PostDate>
              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Hungary looks to be another interesting race with Flouncy taking every pole position at this circuit, and Atomic Lambo following close behind in second place. </p>
<p><strong> Season 1</strong></p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="35" />
<p> </p>
<p><strong> Season 2</strong></p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="54" />
<p> </p>
<p>With Flouncy and Atomic Lambo occupying the top two positions in both seasons, and Eradicator84 on sabatical, the front row of the grid seems to be a foregone conclusion.  The only spanner in the works may be HolyGhost79, but his times are consistent across both seasons, so it's likely he'll only put in a 1:24 something come qualifying day. </p>
<p>What will hapen come race day?  Well, the statistics can once again cast some light on the probability of the result for Season 3</p>
<p><strong>Season 1</strong></p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Race" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="35" />
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Season 2</strong></p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Race" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="54" />
<p> </p>
<p> So it seems likely Atomic Lambo will bring it home in third position and Flouncy should win, ignoring the Season 1 anomoly which was probably the result of an electronics gremlin exiting the pits.</p>
<p>Again, Season 3 should see a deeper field, with possibly 9-10 drivers competiting, which could mix up the results and help bring the season closer together.</p>]]></content>
