            <umbBlogPost id="1387" parentID="1388" level="6" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1053" template="1046" sortOrder="1" createDate="2011-06-30T14:38:17" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:15" nodeName="Threat of FOTA breakaway series looms" urlName="threat-of-fota-breakaway-series-looms" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1057,1079,1306,1388,1387" isDoc="">
              <closeComments>0</closeComments>
              <PostDate>2011-06-30T14:41:00</PostDate>
              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Following recent schedule schanges there has been allegations that F1 rights holder Lambo is favouring certain teams, leaving other teams and drivers at a disadvantage.</p>
<p>Recently the atomic f1 championship has fallen into political turmoil of sorts which saw the withdrawal of 4th placed championship conteder, TurrbalTerror, in protest.  When we interviewed TurrbalTerror he cited FIA bias toward Group Team Lotus and it's drivers, and bending over backwards to accomodate their desires. </p>
<p>This schedule change had a tangible effect on new entrant ET Rom AU who had made special provisions to ensure attendance of the event at the scheduled time.  It was later revealed that ET Rom AU could not make the rescheduled time and the F1 rights holder was unwilling to accept a delayed start, resulting in the smallest grids of the championship season to date.</p>
<p>Thus sparked the withdrawal of TurrbalTerror, who found it hard to continue in the championship when it was clear to him special favours were being handed out, and after he missed 4 races of season 2 in similar circumstances.</p>
<p>Bobaj0rs comments later pulled the scab off the wound and the pus ran free, so to speak, and what seemed like a bottled up tornado of rage was unleased in the FIA / FOTA meeting, where certain teams and drivers expressed a desire for either clarification of the rules, definition of the rules, or even a establishment of a second teir category, leaving the teir 1 drivers: Ghost, Lambo, and Flouncy to battle it out for outright honours.</p>
<p>As is ever the case the smaller teams are complaining of a lack of track time and hoarding of skill, leading to a widening division between teir 1 and teir 2. </p>
<p>Perhaps the rise of Team ROM will help heal the divide, as their two drivers climb up from teir 2 well into teir 1.  While this is probably a tall order during the current season, big things are expected of Team ROM in Season 4, when a raft of new rules and regulations are expected to be introduced.</p>
<p>One of the results of the FIA / FOTA meeting is that any agrievances were allowed to be aired and it was eventually decided that the best way forward is to leave things as they are.  It seems perhaps Lambo is continue where is predecessor, Bernie Eccelestone left off.</p>]]></content>
              <tags><![CDATA[]]></tags>
