            <umbBlogPost id="1394" parentID="1396" level="6" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1053" template="1046" sortOrder="1" createDate="2011-07-04T12:23:47" updateDate="2012-01-11T10:46:15" nodeName="Korean Season 3 race report" urlName="korean-season-3-race-report" writerName="Rob Gray" creatorName="Rob Gray" path="-1,1084,1057,1079,1395,1396,1394" isDoc="">
              <closeComments>0</closeComments>
              <PostDate>2011-07-04T12:32:00</PostDate>
              <metaTitle>
              </metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>
              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[HolyGhost79 retakes the championship lead as the rest of the field get their melee weapons out at turn 1.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>With the battle between Flouncy and HolyGhost79 so close, results in Korea were always going to be hard fought and extremely important to both drivers.   HolyGhost79 grabbed his gauntlet and in true monty python style figuratively slapped Flouncy across the face with it as he threw it down at his opponents feet, with an impressive pole time, 0.2s clear of second placed, and returning driver, TurrbalTerror. </p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="21" />
<p> </p>
<p>As with most races, turn one lap one provided probably the most dangerous corner of the race, with the a near affray as 9 ambitions  were funnelled through one small point in space and time.  While a modicum of respectability was afforded to all at the pointy end, the more ambitious brought the battle to them with TurrbalTerror and Flouncy both forced offline through contact.  Fortunately this gave Ghost time to recover and keep his lead.  ET Rom au then shot one up the port side of the leading pack as they entered turn 2, giving 10 second penalties to both Flouncy and TurrbalTerror. </p>
<p>Once the madness of the first few turns had passed, the pack settled down into a familiar order and by the end of lap one, Ghost and Flouncy were out front doing what it is they do best.  While the strategic skirmish up front played out, the battle for best of the race was raging, with divebombing, spins, slides and tears aplenty.  Atomic Lambo and TurrbalTerror duked it out for 3rd spot, trading blows lap by lap, with TurrbalTerror slowing down to keep the battle alive, finally to away in the last few laps to ensure a podium.  Much to his dismay he’d forgot about the 10 second penalty handed out for his part in the first corner goings on and it was enough to bump him back to fourth and wonder about what could have been.</p>
<p>Much the surprise of even himself, BreakerMorant crossed the finish line in a career best fifth place, earning his HRT team some well needed cash for next season.  The last of the finishes was debutant CruiserComet, who at one point was as high as fourth position on lap 1. </p>
<p>With two races remaining, HolyGhost79 is back in the lead of the championship.</p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Race" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="21" />
<p> </p>]]></content>
              <tags><![CDATA[Korean,race report,flouncy,ghost,holyghost,turrbalterror,battle]]></tags>
