              <content><![CDATA[<p>We've wrapped the most recent season of the ongoing F1 2010 (soon to be F1 2011) full-season championship. Now it's time for a bit of fun. All are welcome to join in these one-off races! Many of our season regulars will be there, and we have room on the grid for those who have the game but for whatever reason weren't able to compete in the championship.<br /><br />What's 'special' about these, then? 100% race distance!  Anything else? <strong>No restrictions on driver aids!</strong> <br /><br />Race details:</p>
<ul>
<li>7pm start on the scheduled Sunday nights. Be online a few minutes before 7 and you'll be invited.</li>
<li>All cars are set to equal performance - so it doesn't matter what car you end up with.</li>
<li>We start with a Qualifying session, then to race.</li>
<li>Damage is on. Tire wear and fuel use is on. Racing rules are on.</li>
</ul>
<p><br /><br />The calendar:</p>
<ul>
<li>Sunday 23rd Jul - Melbourne</li>
<li>Sunday 7th Aug - Suzuka</li>
<li>Sunday 21st August - TBA (let's discuss!)</li>
</ul>
<p><br /><br /><strong>The grid:</strong><br />F1 2010 supports 12 players. The number 'regulars' from the F1 2010 championship vary, some races only half a dozen have turned up, while I think the record is about 10. So! There's a few slots available, and not all the regulars will make all events so post now if you're keen!<br /><br /><br /><strong>Your car:</strong><br />We can't guarantee which car you'll get at this stage, the regulars will likely be racing their preferred cars as follows (but remember all cars are equal so it doesn't actually matter - and not all will be at all races so the car you get is a bit of a lucky dip):<br /><br />Lotus - Ghost<br />McLaren - kikz<br />Red Bull - Flouncy<br />Renault - Lambo<br />Mercedes - Maverick<br />Ferarri - ET<br />Williams - Nobody813<br />HRT - Mac Dude<br />Red Bull - Fredzfrog<br />Sauber - bobaj0r<br /><br /><span>Please indicate if you're 100% gonna be racing, and which events (that goes for everyone!).</span></p>
<p><span>Link to thread where you can register your intersest <a href="http://forums.atomicmpc.com.au/index.php?showtopic=43814&amp;st=0&amp;#entry881169">here</a><br /></span></p>]]></content>
