              </thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>The atomicf1 league ran it's first out of season 100% race distance event at the weekend just gone, and the circuit was Albert Park in Melbourne; everyones home track.  The initial qualifying session saw a few different tactics employed by the top runners, as this more open format gave them a chance to experiment and have some fun.  HolyGhost79 set the outright pace, qualifying on pole with a 1:27s lap.  TurrbalTerror slotted into second place after qualifying on primes, with a 1:29.  The next two places were occupied by AI cars, Kubica and Alonso, before ET ROM took 5th spot.  Surprisingly Flouncy sat out the session, perhaps favouring a fun drive through the pack from the rear.</p>
<p>Qualifying was mooted by the late arrival of roxas3sora3 who had been held up at a sponsor event.  The grid reformed, randomly drawing their grid position from a hat, karting style.  This was enough to give BreakerMorant his first front row slot of the year.</p>
<p><img src="~/media/14716/breakerfrontrow_400x188.jpg"  width="400"  height="188" alt="breakerfrontrow.PNG"/></p>
<p> </p>
<p>The pack got away, but certainly not cleanly, as TurrbalTerror shot one up the inside and collected roxas3sora3 off the start, allowing ET ROM to pull a consistent lead for the first few laps.</p>
<p>A spin TurrbalTerror back to 5th behind Flouncy and HolyGhost79 in 3rd and 4th, and the chase was on for the race victory.  By lap 15 the wet track had dried and it was time for dry tyres.  Some of the pack switched to option tyres, some went out on primes, while others got their radio signals mixed and their crews put them back on wets.</p>
<p>TurrbalTerror remained true to form and smash his nose into a category red break and continued on like that for the next 15 to 20 laps, trying to stay ahead of Flouncy and in particular HolyGhost79, with whom he had an epic battle until again losing it.  This time HolyGhost79 waited up, again keeping the battle going.  TurrbalTerror picked up on the game and not wanting to not win on merit baulked at the overtake, before nailing the throttle, driving past, and spearing into the wall at the next turn.  Flouncy took his opportunity and went through into third.  TurrbalTerror recovered and made it back in front of HolyGhost79 and behind Flouncy, with some perhaps questionable driving, before pitting.</p>
<p>When the 2nd round of stops was done, TurrbalTerror was back in third spot and pulling away from Flouncy, when Flouncy and Ghost decided it was time to engage hyperdrive and reel the erratic Mclaren drive back in.  At that point it was on like donkey kong and the mercedes powered car increased his lead out to 11s only to have it brought back to 8s in traffic, before pulling out a gap again.  Another spin put him back within 3s of Flouncy and it was enough for the Group Force Lotus drive to pounce two laps from the end, when some side by side action through the fastest section of the track saw TurrbalTerror go spearing off.  From there, Flouncy led HolyGhost79 home into 3rd and 4th spots.</p>
<p>Unfortunatley the cameras were never on the rest of the field long enough to get a good picture of what was going on. Probably a lot crashing and spins.</p>]]></content>
