              <teaser><![CDATA[The second out of season race was run last night, to fantastic success, at the Honda owned Suzuka circuit in Japan.  We had 10 starters, made up of some first times, st8tsmann and notjedi, as well as some occasional oldies such as bushipoo, and recent newbies like CruiserComet, as well as stalwarts Flouncy, HolyGhost79, and TurrbalTerror, and more.  ]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>The second out of season race was run last night, to fantastic success, at the Honda owned Suzuka circuit in Japan.  We had 10 starters, made up of some first timers, st8tsmann and notjedi, as well as some occasional oldies such as bushipoo, and recent newbies like CruiserComet, as well as stalwarts Flouncy, HolyGhost79, and TurrbalTerror, and more. </p>
<p>On the books, Suzuka was going to be a Flouncy track.  He dominated the qualifying times here in season 3 and there was strong case the run would continue in this one off 'exhibition' race.  His form was true and he set pole with a 1:33.2.  Perhaps a surprise to Flouncy, but not TurrbalTerror, was TurrbalTerrors second place with a 1:33.5.  He hasn't race at Suzuka since season 1 and while happy with the time, he said it was far from the perfect lap and down on the 1:32.7's he was doing in practice.  2nd place in sesaon qualifier HolyGhost79 slotted into third with a 1:35, consistent with his in season form.  Both TurrbalTerror and HolyGhost79 were handed grid penalties for blocking, dropping then down to 7th and 10th respectively, 5 places for TurrbalTerror and 15 for HolyGhost79.  Both were unjustified.  TurrbalTerror received his after slowing down off line to let following cars by, and HolyGhost79 sufferred steering problems on track.  That drop looked like it would all but hand Flouncy a victory his was likely to take anyway.</p>
<p>Off the line, TurrbalTerror got away well, accelarating hard behind Maverick_ROM in 6th place and st8tsmann in 5th.  TurrbalTerror kept inside on turn one and moved to 6th position, gaining another into turn 2.  ET_ROM shut the door on st8tsmann as he attempted to pass for 2nd, sending the renault car flying off to the left of track and possibly breaking the space-time continum in the process.  St8tsmann seemed to circulate in a universe of his own after that, never seeing another car again, although random ghosts of st8tsmann appeared throughout the race.</p>
<p>With st9tsmann dispatched, ET_ROM set about keeping a fast clearing out Flouncy in-check.  It wasn't going to happen, as Flouncy increased his gap through the essess and TurrbalTerror had now come from 7th to be latched to the back of his gearbox, eventually taking him Dunlop Curve.</p>
<p>As he did in the rain in Valencia, Flouncy showed the world it's possible for double champions to make mistakes and was coming back on track at the hairpin on lap 1 as TurrbalTerror passed him for the lead, 7th to 1st in half a lap, beating Senna's effort in Donnington 1993.</p>
<p>TurrbalTerrors lead wasn't to last long, as Flouncy pushed him hard, and while he wasn't flustered he made an unsual mistake (unsual for this circuit at this event) and ran wide on the fast run into Degner.  With a halfspin, it was enough for Flouncy to just get through on the outside!  For one of two times in 53 laps, TurrbalTerror spun on the exit of Hairpin two corners later and suddenly Flouncy had an 8 second lead. </p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoid="7-7O5q1mRXQ" aspectratio="widescreen" videoheight="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videowidth="600" allowfullscreen="1" />
<p> </p>
<p>As HolyGhost79 made his way up from 10th to 3rd, and in the process apparently breaking the timing devices, the gap between Flouncy and TurrbalTerror remained fairly static, between 6 and 8 seconds.  Over the next 15 laps TurrbalTerror made a few more errors and gap fluctuated it's way to 23 seconds before the leading pair came to lap Maverick_ROM.  Maverick_ROM drove a clean race but as he approached, TurrbalTerror started making mistakes, perhaps second guessing where the Ferrari was going to place itself to allow the McLaren to get by.  He past Maverick_ROM but a spin at the Hairpin allowed the ROManian to unlap himself and running very wide at Spoon incresaed the gap. Finally missing the chicane at Casino Triangle followed by diving into the pits for new primes, meant the next timed lap he was 1:03s down on the leader. </p>
<p>As the midfield battled with a playful HolyGhost79, and echos of st8tsmann would flash through the universe, the gap between first and second rained steady at 63 seconds.  Suddenly TurrbalTerror slowed down to 1st gear.  Did he have a problem?  It turned out he did.  His problem was boredom and acceptance that on this day in the Japanese sun he again didn't have the consistence pace to keep up with Flouncy. </p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO videoheight="" aspectratio="widescreen" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="i7KmnBSQWPk" videourl="" videowidth="600" allowfullscreen="1" />
<p> </p>
<p>What seemed like hours past as the McLaren idled around the track and eventually HolyGhost79 and Maverick_ROM came round to battle for second place.  On fresh option tyres, and the car setup to carry an extra 3 seconds a lap through the Esses, it wasn't going to be a battle but at least it would be fun.  TurrbalTerror and HolyGhost accelarated and braked at random intervals occasionally being punted or getting punted as they toyed with the emotions of the man in red. </p>
<p>It was Maverick_ROM who had the last laugh though, as on the final lap TurrbalTerror was pushed wide and off track by BreakerMorant; the old man not recognising the silver streak on the righthand side.  Maverick_ROM slotted in to second place only 2 laps down on Flouncy.</p>]]></content>
