              <thumbnail>1573</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[McLaren and Team Lotus turned out for pre-season testing on Monday night, 3rd October, at the Melbourne circuit.  Both teams ran strongly and consistently, turning in mid 1:23's laps in race simulations, and lower in private qualifying runs.  ]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/11060/timetrial_397x296.jpg"  width="397"  height="296" alt="timetrial.PNG" style="float: right;"/>McLaren and Team Lotus turned out for pre-season testing on Monday night, 3rd October, at the Melbourne circuit.  Both teams ran strongly and consistently, turning in mid 1:23's laps in race simulations, and lower in private qualifying runs. </p>
<p>McLaren spokesman Rob Gray cited the test session as a major success after evaluating DRS system improvements, which enabled the DRS to stay open for longer than a split second.  Previously, a fault in the DRS switch ment the drag reducing opening would close immediately after it opened.  Once this fault was found and repaired, the McLaren car gained an instant 1.2s in lap time, enabling TurrbalTerror to complete qualifying simuations runs that put him 0.5s up on the second place sitter.</p>
<p>Lotus are also reporting a successul testing session, with improvments in handling resulting in performance upgrades.</p>
<p>Both teams are expected to complete further testing prior to this weekends sesaon opener at Albert Park.</p>]]></content>
