              <metaDescription><![CDATA[Season 4 of the Atomic F1 championship kicks off officially today with the first free practice session for this weekends race.]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1240</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[Season 4 of the Atomic F1 championship kicks off officially today with the first free practice session for this weekends race.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/1453/race_win_flag_400x300.jpg"  width="400"  height="300" alt="Wave Flag" style="float: right;"/>Season 4 of the Atomic F1 championship kicks off officially today with the first free practice session for this weekends race.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Ferrari:</strong> <a href="/{localLink:1268}" title="Flouncy">Flouncy</a>, <a href="/{localLink:1272}" title="BreakerMorant">BreakerMorant</a></p>
<p><strong>Mercedes GP: </strong><a href="/{localLink:1336}" title="ET Rom au">ET ROM</a>, <a href="/{localLink:1390}" title="MaverickROM">MaverickROM</a></p>
<p><strong>Williams</strong>: <a href="/{localLink:1271}" title="Eradicator84">Eradicator84</a>, <a href="/{localLink:1281}" title="roxas3sora3">roxas3sora3</a></p>
<p><strong>Lotus</strong>: <a href="/{localLink:1270}" title="HolyGhost79">HolyGhost79</a>, <a href="/{localLink:1275}" title="Fredzfrog">fredzfrog</a></p>
<p><strong>McLaren: </strong><a href="/{localLink:1266}" title="TurrbalTerror">TurrbalTerror</a>, <a href="/{localLink:1269}" title="bobaj0r">bobaj0r</a></p>
<p><strong>Renault: </strong><a href="/{localLink:1267}" title="Atomic Lambo">Atomic Lambo</a>, <a href="/{localLink:1279}" title="CruiserComet">CruiserComet</a></p>
<p><strong>Red Bull: </strong><a href="/{localLink:1669}" title="notjedi">notjedi</a>, <a href="/{localLink:1670}" title="st8tsman">st8tsman</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>There are a few new drivers this season, notjedi  and st8tsman, as well as one driver returning from sabatical, Eradicator84.  Season 4 will also be the first full season for MaverickROM, ET ROM, and bobaj0r.</p>
<p>This season the FIA has introduced a "Team Skill Level" cap which aims to balance the driver ability of all of the teams and provide a more even playing field in the Constructors battle, making it something of keen interest to all involved.</p>
<p>Season 4 is also the first season the Atomic F1 competition will be run under the F1 2011 rules, including DRS, KERS, and the safety car, something that will no doubt feature heavily in most races and will surely result in some unepxected results and cunning strategy.</p>
<p>Preseason testing at Suzuka has shown the cars to be considerably faster over a single lap than their F1 2010 counterparts and has also introduced a new serious competitor for podiums and wins, ET ROM.  There are now 6 teams out of the 7 registered that are currently capable of wining a race.  As notjedi has yet to put in any track time, Red Bull may also be a contended for wins, making Season 4 easily the most competitive season to date.</p>
<p>The rights holders will also be producing an unprecedented amount of video footage, with four cars now carrying onboard cameras in each race, giving an incockpit view of the action up and down the field.</p>
<p> As ever, Flouncy is expected to top the timesheets from the opening session, though historically Albert Park has been race that has not always gone his way.</p>
<p>While last seasons results aren't particular accurate in light of the rule changes, they may give an indication of outright pace:</p>
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Qualifying" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="6" />
<p> </p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO type="Race" macroAlias="F1InlineRace" raceid="6" />]]></content>
