              <teaser><![CDATA[Ferrari's Flouncy has taken the first race of the season with a controlled drive at Melbourne's Albert after turn 1 carnage.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/3106/little_flounce_398x260.jpg"  width="398"  height="260" alt="Little Flounce" style="float: right;"/>Ferrari's Flouncy has taken the first race of the season with a controlled drive at Melbourne's Albert Park. Despite starting from the second row of the grid the Ferrari looked to have it all under control as he cruised to his third consecutive victory and his seventh win in eight starts since round thirteen of the Italian Grand Prix in Monza during season three. While a comfortable win in the end, it wasn't all to plan with the Ferrari dropping to 8th after the first corner after a tangle with the Mercedes of ET-ROM and Renault of Lambo. However a good recovery and consistent pace saw the Ferrari leapfrog the Renault at the first set of pit stops, and errors from ET-ROM saw him pass for the lead shortly after. The Ferrari never looking troubled after that.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Click <a href="/{localLink:1674}" title="Round 1 Melbourne">here</a> for the full race wrap up.</p>]]></content>
