              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[sepang, malaysia, f12011, atomicf1, preview]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[We preview the Malaysian GP for Season 4 of the Atomic F1 championship.]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1681</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[Who will win in the heat and humidity of Malaysia?  Will it be a wet dry race?  And really, can anybody stop Flouncy?]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="/media/19698/kl-sepang-circuit.jpg" width="300" height="240" alt="kl-sepang-circuit.jpg" style="float: right;"/>Racing in the humitdity and heat of Malaysia is always interesting.  If it's not the sweltering heat, making the body lose litres of fluid, it's the thundering storms making the track a dangerous river with swirling with 19000 brake horse power.</p>
<p>Over the past three seasons Malaysia has seen one man dominant.  Flouncy has held pole and won the race at every Malaysian GP thus far.  Do we expect things to change for season 4?  Unlikely, although I'm sure the hot new talent of ET Rom is going to be trying his hardest to break the stranglehold the double champion has on this circuit.</p>
<p>Maybe with the rules shake up for Season 4 and F12011 spec cars, a new pole sitter will emerge, although it's unlikely that the race result will differ.</p>
<p>What can we expect from the Malaysian GP this season?  Well, action for starters.  Sepang has 15 corners and a few of them contain apexs that are unsighted on entry as well as tightening radiuses, meaning those corners favour the brave and the skilled, or even both.</p>
<p>Some corners to watch out for on race day are the obvious turns 1 and 2 on the initial lap.  The tight nature of turn 1 followed by the switchback for turn 2 is expected to catch a few drivers out and it's anticipated there will be at least 2 spinners at that corner.  The best way to survive is to start further up the grid.  That doens't gaurantee safety though, as a rookie looking to gain places up the inside of turn 1 will likely carry too much speed and take a few scalps with him.</p>
<p>The hairpin turn 9 might also provide some action, as in the past it has proved an overtaking spot for the brave. </p>
<p>Probably the most difficult corner is turn 14, the tightening corner prior to the long back straight.  Exit speed is crucial here if you want to put a move on at turn 15.</p>
<p>My money is on Flouncy for pole. He's just too fast at this circuit.  The podium will be filled by Flouncy, Atomic Lambo, and ET Rom, in that order.  Dark horses will be TurrbalTerror and bobaj0r.  If both can keep their cars pointed forward and remain basically indicent free, McLaren should take constructos honours here.</p>]]></content>
