              <metaTitle>Leggard Previews Sepang Season 4</metaTitle>
              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[sepang, atomicf1, leggard, preview]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[The F1 circus moves to Sepang Malaysia for round two of the the Atomic F1 championship. A favourite amongst the drivers it's long straights are broken up with a mixture of low, medium and high speed corners requiring extreme concentration and providing a real challenge to the drivers. ]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1453</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[The F1 circus moves to Sepang Malaysia for round two of the the Atomic F1 championship. A favourite amongst the drivers it's long straights are broken up with a mixture of low, medium and high speed corners requiring extreme concentration and providing a real challenge to the drivers. ]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/6044/math_400x267.jpg"  width="400"  height="267" alt="math.jpg" style="float: right;"/>The F1 circus moves to Sepang Malaysia for round two of the the Atomic F1 championship. A favourite amongst the drivers it's long straights are broken up with a mixture of low, medium and high speed corners requiring extreme concentration and providing a real challenge to the drivers. With one round in the bag already it's early days in the championship race, however it's never too early to dissect and ponder. For the fans the past week has been about a number of pre-season questions, some of which have been answered, some not and others only when we are well into the season will we know for sure. But until the first qualifying session there's still plenty of time for Jonathan Leggard to check his crystal ball and place a bet on his thoughts for the Malaysian Grand Prix.<br /><br /><strong>In form:</strong><br />If you put money on Flouncy to win at Albert Park you probably didn't did get a very big return. So heavily backed was the Ferrari driver to take the race out with both fans and bookies that there is already talk the championship maybe over. Close to unstoppable in Melbourne and Sepang being a track that he finds more favourite-able, it's hard to put your money elsewhere. <br /><br /><strong>Out of form:</strong><br />Critics agree that the most disappointing drive of last weeks Melbourne Grand Prix was that from Lotus' Ghost. His form last season was near to perfect and he was close to unstoppable in the early flyaway races of season 3. The move to the pirelli, DRS and KERS could be contributing factors, however he'll want to turn around his season fast.<br /><br /><strong>One to watch:</strong><br />ET-Rom picked up from where he left off from pre-season testing with a stunning maiden pole at Albert Park. It's no mistake that he's considered this seasons hot talent, however a few mistakes in the race cost him second place and maybe even the race win. Still in the learning process, but it would seem that taking the next step is only a matter of time.<br /><br /><strong>Talking points:</strong><br />The question on everyones lips is can Ferrari's Flouncy be stopped. While some say it's too early to tell, not everyone has been able to fully adapt to the change in rules, especially with higher degradation of the perelli tires. What ever the reason some go as far to predict the most dull season so far if he remains unchallenged.<br /><br /><strong>Fast facts:</strong><br />- This will be the 4th Malaysian GP in Atomic F1 history. Flouncy has won every Malaysian GP so far.<br />- Qualifying record: Flouncy 1:34.972<br /><br /><strong>The circuit:</strong><br />Designed by "the architect of F1", Hermann Tilke, Sepang is considered one of the most technical circuits on the calendar and is a firm favourite with the drivers. The combination of long, high-speed, straights and tight corner complexes were designed with overtaking in mind. <br /><br /><strong>Betting:</strong><br />There no question who the fans favour to take out his 4th Malaysian GP win, Flouncy will be looking to add his Australian GP trophy and all but cement his championship favourite status. Flouncy 2/1, Lambo 8/1, Ghost now slips to 15/1. Worth putting an each way bet on ET-Rom, 12/1.<br /><br /><strong>Leggard prediction:</strong><br />You can't pass up Flouncy. 3 wins from 3 starts at this track, he might be troubled if it rains, but it's almost certain he'll put a 4th win on his CV.</p>]]></content>
