              <metaDescription><![CDATA[Could Ferrari and world champion Flouncy be stumbling at the blocks for the Malaysian GP.]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1688</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[Could Ferrari and world champion Flouncy be stumbling at the blocks for the Malaysian GP?]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Team Ferrari has received a major setback to its training and development program, with the recent release of Might and Magic: Heroes IV.<br /><br />The Ferrari #1 driver, Flouncy de la Flounce, has been spending many precious hours which were planned for on-track testing in the new game, which has been described as "magically addictive" and "so pretty".<br /><br />Ferraro team supremo Stefano Domenicali insists this is no cause for concern, and is simply a planned strategic part of Flouncy's stress management program.<br /><br />When asked when de la Flounce will resume on-track development duties, Domenicali explained that his star driver was currently "off with the fairies" and is expected to make an appearance after "just one more turn."</p>]]></content>
