              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[Sepang, Malaysia, atomicf1, race, midfield, excitement,f1 2011]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[Sepang expected to produce battles up and down the field as drivers begin to sort out an early season pecking order, getting down to business after the party atmosphere of the Australian Grand Prix.]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1209</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[Sepang expected to produce battles up and down the field as drivers begin to sort out an early season pecking order, getting down to business after the party atmosphere of the Australian Grand Prix.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>By Andrew Benson<br /><br /><img src="~/media/1155/racestart_399x250.jpg"  width="399"  height="250" alt="racestart" style="float: right;"/>After a cracking season that has both surprised and disappointed spectators, the focus now moves towards Sepang. The new rules of a rookie driver with an established driver seemed to work wonders as we have seen close running throughout Albert Park. Most surprising was the result in which roxas3sora3 takes 4th place from a hard charging HolyGhost79 in 5th. "It was tough really. I thought he'll get by within a lap but I kept my head down and just do what I did best." a humble roxas3sora3 described in the pits afterwards. However, he is adamant that HolyGhost79 will one up coming Malaysia. "I don't like Malaysia as it's all about risks and something I can't learn that quickly."<br /><br />HolyGhost79 was disappointed in his result but was confident that he'll bounce back in Malaysia. "Malaysia is one of my favourite tracks. Given the layout and the possibility of rain, it's the place where I'll start my championship." And given the history of the circuit, it is a rough split of 50% rain and 50% dry.<br /><br />Martin Whitmarsh has been highly excited at Malaysia. "I'm confident we've got all the necessary means to win in Malaysia." TurrbalTerror is quietly confident at Malaysia too. "The car is running well ever since we arrived since this week. Bobaj0r has been helping out fine tune the issues in getting the car ready for race."<br /><br />Defending world champion Flouncy has been quiet over the up-down performance of his team. "At the moment, we're steadily improving the car and as well as BreakerMorant. He's still a junior but we should be able to get by." Some had questioned over the use of coded messages between Breaker and Flouncy during the Melbourne race compared to the straight messages the other teams have been using. One such compatriot, st8smn, has been at the receiving end of this given his DNF was the result of these messages. "All I heard was 'the train is entering the tunnel' and I lost it because I was laughing so much!"<br /><br />Renault team boss Eric Boullier had high praise for CruiserComet in his rookie run at Melbourne. "He was doing fine in comparison to all the rookies. He managed to be in 6th and holding off Eradicator, TurrbalTerror and as well as Fredzfrog. At the rate he's progressing, he should be a midfielder soon."<br /><br />Team Lotus was disappointed that the pre-season preparations hadn't come to fruition. "It's disappointing that we finished quite down on the order in Melbourne but due to incidents out of our hand, we're quite lucky to get this result." Mike Gascoyne was a lot more optimistic about Malaysia. "Malaysia is where we expect both team members to shine." Asked about Fredzfrog's driving style, the blunt reply was "What about it? Do you see Michael Schumacher being questioned over his driving style?"<br /><br />With that, all eyes turn to the qualifying tomorrow night.</p>]]></content>
