              <metaDescription><![CDATA[The Atomic F1 circus arrives in the booming nation of China this weekend for round 4 of the championship.  The question on everyones lips this weekend is can Flouncy bounce back to form and mount a challenge to the re-invigorated bobaj0r.]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1713</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[The Atomic F1 circus arrives in the booming nation of China this weekend for round 4 of the championship.  The question on everyones lips this weekend is can Flouncy bounce back to form and mount a challenge to the re-invigorated bobaj0r.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/21138/chinese-flag_400x264.jpg"  width="400"  height="264" alt="chinese-flag.PNG" style="float: right;"/>The Atomic F1 circus arrives in the booming nation of China this weekend for round 4 of the championship.  The question on everyones lips this weekend is can Flouncy bounce back to form and mount a challenge to the re-invigorated bobaj0r.</p>
<p>Qualifying position at Shanghai will be paramount. With the a difficult off-camber changing radius turn 1/2, it's expected that, like all previous Chinese grand prix's the start will be havoc. With the increased grid size in Season 4, this problem will only be magnifed, as any off will mean having to wait for the entire field of 16 to go by, and mkaing catching the leaders even more difficult.</p>
<p>One driver who shouldn't find this a problem is the double world champion Flouncy, who holds the current lap record around this circuit, some 3 seconds faster than the next best time, held by one bobaj0r. </p>
<p>That's not to say Atomic Lambo should be discounted.  He has featured strongly here in the past, at a circuit he regards as one of the biggest technical challenges on the calendar.  HolyGhost79 is also another strong runner, although his perofrmance of late have been less than the same time in Season 3 and his attendance at this GP is not yet assured, after voicing his feeling anti-communism put him high on the terror watch list with the peoples republic.</p>
<p>Shanghai will be a new circuit for many of the new drivers, including the Mercdes teammates ET ROM and MaverickROM, the later of whom desparately needs to improve his form after a lackluster opening races.  The Chinese GP will also be the debut of Modz, driving for the Sauber team and his appearance will no doubht through a spanner in the works of some of the established drivers.</p>
<p>Tyre wear and engines in Shanghai will be critical, as that long back straight has already destroyed a few engines in practice.  A wise strategy may be to run a long 7th gear.</p>
<p>I expect a three way battle for victory between Flouncy, Atomic Lambo, and bobaj0r, with ET Rom, Eradicator, TurrbalTerror and HolyGhost79, if he appears, fighting out a close battle for fourth spot.</p>
<p>The third pack will likely be made up of MaverickROM, CruiserComet, and roxas3sora3, with the rest of the field including NIGHTKID2, who is looking to have a better start than in Malaysia, Modz, fredzfrog, notjedi, st8smn350, and the ever improving BreakerMorant, who has already notched up some runs on the board.</p>
<p>Time to get the chopsticks out and say hello to the East.  It's the Chinese GP race wekeend!</p>]]></content>
