              <metaDescription><![CDATA[]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1717</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[Following on from Shanghai, Istanbul Park is another one of the modern F1 tracks that have been designed by Hermann Tilke. Bobaj0r is favourite to take out his second race and stamp a claim on the championship at 3/1 odds.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><strong>Who's in for a Turkish delight?</strong><br />After a week break following what was a breathless Chinese Grand Prix, the Atomic Formula One paddock finally gets on the European roads this weekend with a trip to Turkey. Lambo took his first race victory of the season winning in Shanghai, but with only 15 points seperating him from Flouncy and the Renault driver not able to make the grid in Istanbul, we will likely see a new championship leader after this weekend. With 3 races in and 3 different winners, will we see a new race winner crowned? Or will someone start to stamp their authority on this season?<br /><br /><strong>In Form</strong><br />Having secured his first win of the Season and so far not having finished worse than 2nd, the Renault of Lambo is riding a wave of confidence. However since he won't be starting this weekends race and is therefore out of the hunt for any points we turn our attention to bobaj0r. Since missing Melbourne he's fought back with a stunning win in Malaysia, and a second in China. Confidence is high for the McLaren driver and with no Lambo on the grid has to be considered the race favourite at this time.<br /><br /><strong>Out of Form</strong><br />Ghosts depressing start to the season continued at China ruing a bad tire strategy and suffering from a number of run ins on the track. Considering his capabilities and the start he had to season 3 many in the paddock hoped for big things this season. Turkey should be a happier hunting ground having stepped on the podium last season.<br /><br /><strong>One to watch</strong><br />It would be unfair to say Flouncy's 7th in Malaysia and 3rd in China are a sign of a slump in form, but it's clear the Ferrari driver isn't entirely happy. However he has won this race and will look to put things right. One to watch.<br /><br /><strong>Talking Points</strong><br />Turn 8 - While Hermann Tilke's tracks have not always been the subject of immense praise, it's pretty clear that the greatest corner he has designed is an original - the multi-apex turn 8. Taken at an average speed of over 160mph, Red Bull were famously able to take the corner flat out last year. Drivers experience up to 5G of lateral force through the turn, and expect to see plenty of cars snapping off line during practice and qualifying. <br /><br /><strong>Fast Facts</strong><br />- This will be the 4th Turkish Grand Prix, previous winners, S1 - Ghost, S2 - Flouncy, S3 - TurrbalTerror<br />- The pole sitter has never won the race.<br />- Qualifying record - 1:26.339 - bobaj0r<br />- There are 14 corners on the circuit, but one - turn 8 - accounts for 40% of the tyre wear per lap due to its long high-speed nature. The cars are at full throttle for 8.5 seconds, putting a huge load on the front right tyre as the drivers experience an average of 3.5 lateral G.<br /><br /><strong>Curcuit</strong><br />Following on from Shanghai, Istanbul Park is another one of the modern F1 tracks that have been designed by Hermann Tilke. While everybody talks about the high-speed turn 8, Tilke has made good use of the undulations which sees a total elevation change of nearly 46 metres. The track mainly consists of medium to high-speed corners, with potential overtaking chances down in to turn 1 and turn 9. The best opportunity, however, comes after the long uphill back straight (interrupted by a right kink nicknamed 'Faux Rouge') in to the heavy braking zone for turn 12. Good traction is required for the slow complex of corners at the end of the lap before returning on to the pit straight. <br /><br /><strong>Betting</strong><br />Bobaj0r is favourite to take out his second race and stamp a claim on the championship at 3/1 odds. Next is Flouncy at 6/1, Ghost 9/1, Modz is worth putting an each way bet at 14/1, with ET-ROM coming in at 16/1. TurrbalTerror has had good fortunate at this track but starts just inside ET at 12/1.<br /><br /><strong>Leggard Prediction</strong><br />This season has been a seesaw of favourites, but going on current form it's hard to go past bobaj0r to put another trophy in the cabinet. <br />It would be unfair to say Flouncy's 7th in Malaysia and 3rd in China are a sign of a slump in form, but it's clear the Ferrari driver isn't entirely happy. However he has won this race and will look to put things right. One to watch.</p>]]></content>
