              <teaser><![CDATA[McLaren downbeat on Turkish chances.  Team prays for safe return of bobaj0r from the war zone.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>McLaren Press Officer Rob Gray today expressed his concern over the McLaren teams chances of success at this weekends Turkish Grand Prix.</p>
<p>Current team points leader bobaj0r has been called up for military service on the Battlefield for the near future, with only a short release from his military duties to participate in the atomic f1 events.  Team development driver TurrbalTerror is uncharacteristically struggling to find a stable setup for the notoriously edgy mercedes powered car.</p>
<p>Despite bobajor given 3/1 odds for winning from bookmakers, after a successful run built on solid setup development by TurrbalTerror, McLaren does not rate the current #1 contender so highly for this weekends race.</p>
<p>Unless TurrbalTerror can find a setup that works in the next few days, it is unlikely the Turkish event will be one to remember: Unfortunate, considering the pair locked out the front row last year and TurrbalTerror led the field to take his and teams only win of the season.</p>
<p>McLaren as a team are hoping their Season 4 star driver makes it back in one piece for the race.</p>]]></content>
