              <metaDescription><![CDATA[After a clash with the Real World Indian F1 GP, the field has thinned for the fourth race of the fourth season of atomic f1]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1736</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[After a clash with the Real World Indian F1 GP, the field has thinned for the fourth race of the fourth season of atomic f1]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Hot the heals of the withdrawal of Atomic Lambo from Turkish GP, Team Vodafone Merdeces McLaren announced the withdrawal of bobaj0r after an already shortened preparation period. </p>
<p>The FIA released a statement confirming a clash with the Real World Indian GP which is scheduled to start at 1930 EDST, 30 mins before the start of the Atomic F1 round in Turkey.  Atomic F1 Commercial rights holder Ben Mansill has confirmed the the Atomic F1 GP will not be rescheduled to accomodate those wishing to watch the GP, and that in this modern era, recording the event for later viewing is a suitable alternative.</p>]]></content>
