              <thumbnail>1453</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[The absence of two top runners this weekend leaves the championship wide open.  Here is what the championship table will most likley look like following this race.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/6044/math_400x267.jpg"  width="400"  height="267" alt="math.jpg" style="float: right;"/>With runaway points leader Atomic Lambo missing this weekends Grand Prix, and third place bobaj0r also out, the points table is set for a shake-up.</p>
<p>Based on testing form, current race form and last years results, the most likely results from this weekends race sees the podium filled by TurrbalTerror, HolyGhost79, and Flouncy, all of whom are battling their own form slumps or problems of late.</p>
<p>If TurrbalTerror leads  home HolyGhost79, followed by Flouncy, in a repeat of last seasons results, the points table will look like</p>
<ol>
<li>Atomic Lambo - 61</li>
<li>Flouncy - 61</li>
<li>TurrbalTerror - 52</li>
<li>HolyGhost79 - 52</li>
<li>ET Rom - 47</li>
<li>bobaj0r - 43</li>
</ol>
<p>This is probably the best result for Atomic Lambo and bobaj0r.  Nearly just as likely is a HolyGhost win with Flouncy coming home second, followed by TurrbalTerror in third.</p>
<ol>
<li>Flouncy - 64</li>
<li>Atomic Lambo - 61</li>
<li>HolyGhost79 - 68</li>
<li>ET Rom - 47</li>
<li>TurrbalTerror - 44</li>
<li>bobajor - 43</li>
</ol>
<p>Where we'll see the top of the championship ladder break into two groups of Flouncy, Atomic Lambo, and HolyGhost79, with ET rom heading up group 2 infront of TurrbalTerror and bobaj0r.</p>
<p>In the event Flouncy wins ahead of TurrbalTerror, and HolyGhost79 the championship would start to look like seasons of old much earlier than we'd all like.</p>
<ol>
<li>Flouncy - 71</li>
<li>Atomic Lambo - 61</li>
<li>HolyGhost79 - 49</li>
<li>ET Rom - 47</li>
<li>TurrbalTerror - 45</li>
<li>bobaj0r - 43</li>
</ol>
<p>There's also some good points on grab for drivers further down the grid, with a battle 5th plce to be fought out between Eradicator84 and roxas3sora3,</p>
<p>The race should also see McLaren take the lead in the constructors title.</p>]]></content>
