              <teaser><![CDATA[FIA Officials have handed down a one race suspension to NightKid2 as a result of incidents in this race and previous races, after a warning following events in Turkey.  ]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>FIA Officials have handed down a one race suspension to NightKid2 as a result of incidents in this race and previous races, after a warning following events in Turkey. </p>
<p>ET Rom placed NightKid2 on report after contant in the first lap put him into a spin, and contact later in the race also spun him round.</p>
<p>FIA Official Ben Mansill released the following statement regarding the suspension:</p>
<blockquote><em>The number 1 priority for all of us when we race is not to cause our friends in other cars to come off, and have their race ruined by our actions.  Finishing position comes after that as a lower priority.  You're still a rookie. You have yet to learn on-track racecraft.</em><br /><br /><em>When you see us on track, and if the videos of us lot look like we're getting real close, that's because we've been racing together for years. We know the cars, the tracks - and each other's driving styles. We trust each other. We know how to pass, we understand the difference between contact that will just make a noise, and contact that will throw someone out.</em><br /><br /><em>You are not at that level yet.</em><br /><br /><em>But, your raw car speed is. That's good. It means you have plenty of scope to think about driving safely, as you drive. You have the car control needed to be able to handle heavy traffic, and exercise simple passes. But you still drive in the manner one would against AI.</em><br /><br /><em>I've seen you take great care to give other cars room, but I've also seen you make reckless moves that have pushed others off the track -- moves that we're never gonna happen cleanly, no matter who was at the wheel in those positions, and shouldn't have been attempted. Just one or two of those in a season can make a driver's bad reputation. You're doing it at least a couple of times a race.</em><br /><br /><em>Now, again, accusations are flying and you're the center of it again. Your explanations earlier on this page regarding incidents with ET Rom do not match the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iclqSVkpKV0&amp;feature=channel_video_title" target="_blank">video evidence</a>.</em><br /><br /><em><strong>Over ambitious, too aggressive - and with a focus entirely on getting past the car in front whatever the cost. </strong></em><br /><br /><em>You're so close to being someone we look forward to racing with. But this keeps happening. And you're indignant and defensive when you should be humble and apologetic. </em><br /><br /><br /><em><strong>Take a one race break. </strong></em><br /><br /><br /><em>We'll see you week after next at Canada, where your driving will be watched closer than ever. </em><br /><br /><em>Races are long, they are strategic. They are not turn-by-turn dogfights. Know your place Tim. You are new and you need to earn our trust.</em></blockquote>]]></content>
