              <thumbnail>1788</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[Every season we see intense rivalry between the top drivers. In season one and two it was Flouncy and Lambo, season three Flouncy and Ghost. Could we be seeing the start of another rivalry in Bobaj0r and Lambo who came to blows on the opening corner of Monaco? ]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><strong>The challenge of Canada</strong><br />Once again the Formula One paddock descends on the Circuit Gilles Villeneuve in Canada to contest round 7 of the Atomic Formula One Championship. While all eyes turn to the 4.36km circuit for the 4th running of this race, all tongues are still waging from the extraordinary events of the Monaco Grand Prix. Every season we see intense rivalry between the top drivers. In season one and two it was Flouncy and Lambo, season three Flouncy and Ghost. Could we be seeing the start of another rivalry in Bobaj0r and Lambo who came to blows on the opening corner of Monaco? Time will tell but there's no doubt McLaren will be out for revenge and Renault will be desperate to claw back a lead after not scoring in both Monaco and Istanbul now. The scene is set for an explosive and exciting Canadian Grand Prix.<br /><br /><strong>In Form</strong><br />Once again bobaj0r needs a mention, despite the result in Monaco is still showing worrying pace for his competitors. Goes into Canada still with a healthy 14 point lead over the Ferrari of Flouncy. A special mention however should go to Ghost who despite starting last on the grid in the last race had a stunning win.<br /><br /><strong>Out of Form</strong><br />Renault will be desperate to get their championship charge back on track and right the wrongs of Monaco. Slipping in both the constructors and drivers championship this will be considered a make or break round now. <br /><br /><strong>One to watch</strong><br />Like a light bulb being switched on the Lotus of ghost has catapulted up the rankings after his unlikely win in Monaco. Perhaps this result is just the motivation needed to kick-start his season and with the Lotus driver being the defending race winner from Season 3 it could be a very close battle up the grid. One to watch.<br /><br /><strong>Talking points</strong><br /><em>DRS</em> - Having highlighted its importance at many races this year, once again the DRS is going to be a focal point in Canada. For the first time there will be two DRS zones; one on the Droit du Casino and the second on the start/finish straight after the chicane. There's only one detection point, so the idea is to give the following car a better chance to overtake if they can't get past at the first zone. It's likened to Melbourne, where a car closed on the run down to turn one, but couldn't pass, and then would have been helped by having the system available again on the run down to turn three. Only the car that is behind at the detection point can use it, so if a pass occurs before the chicane, the other driver can't use the DRS to fight back in the second zone. <br /><br /><em>Soft tyres</em> - The tyres are a talking point yet again, as the soft and super-soft compounds will be available as in Monaco. The race in Canada last year saw high levels of degredation, leading to such an exciting race that it was actually the catalyst for Pirelli being given the brief to produce rapidly-wearing tyres to make races more entertaining. That occurred on last year's much harder Bridgestone rubber, so what is going to be the result on this season's tyres is anyone's guess. <br /><br /><strong>Fast Facts</strong><br />- This will be the fourth Canadian Grand Prix - Previous winners S1, S2 - Lambo, S3 - Ghost<br />- Lambo has never not been on pole here with 3 poles from 3 starts.<br />- Lowest grid position this race has been won from is 3rd.<br />- The qualifying record is 1:14.227 set by Lambo in S3. Sure to be smashed.<br /><br /><strong>Real Life Facts</strong><br />- Canada is another circuit that is renowned for its safety car periods due to the close proximity of the walls around the circuit. In 2007 when Lewis Hamilton took his maiden grand prix victory he had to negotiate four separate safety car periods.<br />- The circuit used to be called the Circuit Ile Notre-Dame after the island it is built on, but was renamed in 1982 following Gilles Villeneuve's death at Zolder that year.<br />- The wall on the outside of the final chicane is known as the 'Wall of Champions' after former world champions Damon Hill, Michael Schumacher and Jacques Villeneuve all retired after crashing in to it during the 1999 race.<br />- In 1982, pole sitter Didier Pironi stalled on the line, and although most of the grid managed to avoid him, Riccardo Paletti was unsighted having started from the back of the grid and crashed heavily in to the rear of the Ferrari. Paletti died from his injuries later in hospital. <br /><br /><strong>Circuit</strong><br />Canada is a high-speed, low downforce track where cars run special aero specifications. The circuit's long straights make a good top speed a necessity, while it is also a tough track on brakes. There are seven braking zones in total, of which six are considered to be 'heavy' and four of those require the driver to brake from over 295kph. Turn ten is the heaviest braking zone as cars decelerate from 295kph to 60kph in just 140m. As a result brake wear is always a factor, with teams sacrificing about 0.2s per lap in performance by running larger brake ducts to help cooling. Being a part-time circuit the track surface is not overly abrasive, but the cars need to be able to ride the kerbs well. The main overtaking opportunities occur in to turn one, turn eight and in to the final chicane. <br /><br /><strong>Betting</strong><br />bobaj0r is the bookies favourite still despite not having a great record here at 5/1 odds. Ghost is the most improved with his win here last season at 8/1 with Lambo not far behind at 9/1. Flouncy is a dark horse here despite not winning here either and is worth a look at 10/1.<br /><br /><strong>Leggard Prediction</strong><br />It looks like the championship is hotting up and top runners are starting to make their claims. I'm going to tip Ferrari's Flouncy to take his first win at the Circuit Gilles Villeneuve.</p>]]></content>
