              <metaKeywords><![CDATA[Valencia, season 4, preview, atomicf1, race]]></metaKeywords>
              <metaDescription><![CDATA[Valencia is a semi-street circuit around the industrial area of an insdustrial Spanish city.  A high downforce circuit with a few straights thrown in for good measure.]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1811</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[Valencia is a semi-street circuit around the industrial area of an insdustrial Spanish city.  A high downforce circuit with a few straights thrown in for good measure.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>Valencia is like Monaco without the glamour and the history, or the challenge.  Considered one of the most boring circuits on the calendar, last seasons race was action packed, as the grid lined up on a very very wet circuit.</p>
<p>Season 4 Valencia marks the first race of the new specification cars, with 8/8 spring limits lifted but car handling subtley altered.  Who will best come to terms with the new regulations will be shown. Perhaps a new challenger will emerge.</p>
<p><strong>bobaj0r<br /></strong>Previously not particular fast at Valencia, with a 3rd and a 4th place.  After a stunning season thus far he's not expected to slow down and should start from the front row of the grid and finish on the podium.  Based on this seasons run, the most likely driver to win<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>Flouncy<br /></strong>Previous pole sitter and Valencia afficionda, Flouncy will be out to close the gap to bobaj0r. After disappointing lack of pace at the Canadian grand prix, he's in with a good chance for the race win and based on previous results here, the most likely to start from pole.</p>
<p><strong>Atomic Lambo<br /></strong>The current aggregate Valencia winner, Atomic Lambo will likely start on the front row of the grid and battle bobaj0r for the race victory.  If bobaj0r doens't start from pole, Atomic Lambo will be favourite to win the race<strong>.  </strong>He's not finished less than 2nd this year.  <strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>HolyGhost79<br /></strong>Lately in a form slump that saw him put on his worst performance of his career, the season 3 runner up will be trying to re-capture his winning ways but is unlikely to challenge the top three drivers.  If he can get away clean, and qualifying well, he'll probably run home a solid 4th place.  His objective for this weekend is probably just to prevent TurrbalTerror closing in on him in the points standings.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>TurrbalTerror<br /></strong>Consistently the back of the front, TurrbalTerrors goals are to finish ahead of Eradicator84 and reduce the points gap to HolyGhost79<strong>.  </strong>Excluding his 10 place grid penalty in Melbourne, following steering failure, he has the 2nd best qualifying average of the grid, at 2.33.  It's statistically likely the McLarens will sit 1 and 2 on the grid, and on this street circuit, where passing may prove difficult, TurrbalTerror, as in Canada, might again prove to be a big stumbling block for Flouncy and Atomic Lambo if they want a shot at victory this weekend.  <strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>ET_Rom_au<br /></strong>ET Rom is out in the wilderness of sorts in the last couple of races, and although reporting initial problems with the ver 2.0 specifications for season 4, these changes provide him with an opportunity to improve his position and claw back some points on TurrbalTerror, only 4 points in front in the driver standings.  4th place will be his likely best result.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>Eradicator84<br /></strong>Always a high runner, Eradicator84 has previously done very well at Valencia and will surely be looking to stamp his unique style of driving on the track this weekend.  Likely qualifying mid pack, he'll surely surge up through field and be pushing for 4th or 3rd by quarter distance.  Another strong contender for that 4th place position.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>roxas3sora3<br /></strong>With an average result of 7.5 at Valencia, this race is sora's change to improve as a possible 5th or 6th place finish is beckoning. If he can stay out of the barriers and out of contact from other drivers, in the hard fought mid-pack, he should finish well.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>NightKid2<br /></strong>Likely making his return after a 1 race ban and missing 1 race of his own decision, Valencia gives NightKid2 an opportunity to show he can drive cleanly and still carry the pace he's becoming renowned for.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>CruiserComet<br /></strong>After a frustrating disconnection in Canada, CrusierComet is looking forward to an interruption free race in Valencia and will hopefully be battling it out with roxas3sora3 for 6th position.  Perhaps he struggles the with a flow of information from the other side of the Lotus garage<strong>.<br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>BreakerMorant<br /></strong>If he's in attendance this weekend, Breaker will be looking to make the recently released footage of his career look silly, by showing his no mobile chicane.  The most life-experienced driver on the grid will be out to show CruiserComent who's boss.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>Modz85<br /></strong>Another dark horse, Modz85, if he can stay connected with the race track, may be in for a blinder. He could even finish first amongst those that have not yet won a race.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>st8smn350<br /></strong>Should have a good race here.  His connection issues seem to be sorted out, or at least improved the time being and hopefully he'll show some of the pace he had during pre-season testing.  If so, the front runners will be concerned and we could have our drive of the race.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>Fredzfrog<br /></strong>Season 4 backmaker, FredzFrog is hoping to recapture his speed from last year and if so will give at least a few of the drivers above him a lesson in driving.</p>
<h3>Constructors</h3>
<p>There's little to talk about here, other than Mclaren's complete domination of the field.  In what is now a very unbalanced team compared to the others, the Mclaren juggernaut will not be stopped this season.  The only glimmer of hope for the other teams is that the FIA will likely break the team apart at the end of the season as they strive for more parity between the teams.</p>]]></content>
