              <teaser><![CDATA[Mclaren, Mercedes, and Williams complete Friday practice at Valencia]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p>The Friday practice session at Valencia has ended after two 20% race simulations, including qualifying. </p>
<p>Run 1 was held in wet conditions for the qualifying session, with TurrbalTerror and Mclaren taking pole by over two seconds.  The practice was a dry affair though and TurrbalTerror pulled out a 6 second lead by halfway round the 2nd lap, where he promptly pulled over to sip his latte while the other drivers, Eradicator84, roxas3sora3 and ET_Rom made their way around the circuit.</p>
<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoid="WMNRpZpy5ms" aspectratio="" videoheight="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videowidth="" allowfullscreen="0" />
<p>The session ended with TurrbalTerror winning the race with a race fastest lap 1.6s faster than Eradicator84, the third place finisher and 2nd fastest race lap.  All other drivers also lapping within 0.3s of Eradicator84, in a confidence boosting drive for roxas3sora3.</p>
<p>The second qualifying session was dry and allowed all drivers to turn the wick up. Again it was TurrbalTerror posting the fastest time, some 2.2s faster than 2nd fastest time of Eradicator84.  Again, Eradicator84, ET ROM au, and roxas3sora3 were seperated by less than 0.2s</p>
<p>The race session was also dry and this time TurrbalTerror had no coffee to stop and drink and drove 11 mistake free laps to take the flag 20seconds ahead of Eradicator84.  In a confidence booster for the race for Eradicator84, this time his fastest race lap was only 0.5s slower than the Mclarens fastest, although still 1.1s slower than the time the McLaren set in race 1.  roxas3sora3 also set a race best lap time 0.1s faster than ET rom au, but still 1.0s adrift of his teammate.</p>
<p>Sunday's race looks like be a competitive affair through the pack.</p>]]></content>
