              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/26519/silverstone_400x267.jpg"  width="400"  height="267" alt="silverstone.jpg" style="float: right;"/>This weekends race at Silverstone presents the first opportunity to provide a more level playing field for new competitors. The Silverstone circuit has been revised since 2010, with the pits and start finish line moved half way round the track, as well as a reprofiling of moving of some of the corners leading into the new pit lane.  While not a big difference it's may help new drivers finish higher up that previously. </p>
<p>Initial laps of the circuit have shown the 2011 performance gap comparative to 2010 is not as high here as at other circuits, noteably the last race in Valencia.  Running a default setup on primes yielded a lap time comparable with last years pole position, rather than the 4 seconds faster Mclaren were seeing on the default setup at Valencia.</p>]]></content>
