              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/26651/F1_Red_Bull_Christmas_Card_600x400.jpg"  width="600"  height="400" alt="F1_Red_Bull_Christmas_Card.jpg" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"/></p>
<p>'tis the season to be merry...</p>
<p>Atomic F1 is proposing a break from competitions during the chirstmas new year period. It's proposed the last race will be held on December 18 and racing will recommence on January 8, if this is suitable for everyone.  If not, please proprose a new time on the <a href="http://forums.atomicmpc.com.au/index.php?showtopic=45163&amp;pid=934941&amp;st=2200&amp;#entry934941">forum</a> or in the comments.</p>
<p>As always, this doens't mean there can't be non-official events any any time, amongst the competitors and other interested parties.  Realistically, this is an ideal opportunity for people to get in some valuable practice ahead of the second half the season. </p>
<p>FIA has mandated that all team members must be allowed to spend time with their families, and the middle of this 19 race long season is a good time for this.</p>]]></content>
