              <metaDescription><![CDATA[Waffles and fun at Spa]]></metaDescription>
              <thumbnail>1860</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[The grid has turned upside down and back-to-front for the Belgian Grand Prix.  Results may shock.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><img src="~/media/28428/SPA_Francorchamps_track_by_arthobald_400x267.jpg"  width="400"  height="267" alt="Spa at night" style="float: right;"/>Some come for the waffles, some come for the beer, all come for Eu Rougue. Hosting the most infamous corner in F1, Spa Franchorchamp is also a tour de fource everywhere else. Set on hilly landscape, this the longest circuit on the calendar twists and turns at high speed as the cars go through numerous and dramatic elevation changes. </p>
<p>We also welcome back the F1 circus after a three week, tools down layoff, for the Christmas period.  Some drivers chose to do nothing, some went skiiing, some drove in other categories.  Some even left the series.</p>
<p>In big news ET Rom au has changed from Mercedes to Ferrari, joining Flouncy, in an attempt by the Scuderia to create a team that can challenge the deflating Mclaren squad.  Mercedes, after losing its last drive has poached Nightkid2 and Modz85 from Sauber.   Other big news is the likely mid-season retirement of championship leader and tour de fource bobaj0r, who has been silent for over a month.  It's possible he may return for this race but he may not be at full strength for the Mclaren team, leaving a lot of valuable points up for grabs from the other drivers.</p>
<p>In other big news, HolyGhost79 has had his internet connection upgraded and should now no longer want to start from the rear, meaning another of the big-guns has returned to the front, not that a back of the grid start ever prevented HolyGhost from scoring a podum finish or race win.</p>
<p>Had Mclaren continued to race Hungrary and practice through the offseason it would have been likely they'd have continued their domination of the podium, but now that seems unlikely at best.  Another quiet driver is Atomic Lambo and Renault, who typically does his talking only on the track. </p>
<p>This weekends race should see Flouncy take pole from HolyGhost79 and both battle it out for the top spot of the podium. Thrown into that mix should be Atomic Lambo who generally finishes either 2nd or 1st so can't be discounted.  A darkhorse is ET Rom, who under the tutelage of Flouncy should challenge for the bottom step of the podium if he can qualify well and keep his nose intact. </p>]]></content>
