              <thumbnail>1688</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[We recently sat down with the erstwhile Williams driver and picked his brain.  Read the results here.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><b><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></b><b>Q: You must get rid of a course that you raced so far in your AtomicF1 career - which do you choose, and why?</b><br />Bahrain easily. Boring and not that exciting. I was happy that Bahrain was removed for this season. A close second would be Valencia. It's just too long and easy to make mistakes in it.<br /><br /><b>Q: If you could choose a Atomic world champion as your team mate, who would you choose and why?</b><br />Lambo easily. Flouncy would deck my arse hard so having Lambo would be interesting to have as a team mate.<br /><br /><b>Q: What rules or innovations would you like to see in the future?</b><br />Bring back refuelling. Having to choose when to come in for fuel and tyres would be hard to beat.<br /><br /><b>Q: You can only drive at one circuit for the rest of your life - which AtomicF1 circuit, past or present from anywhere in the world, do you choose?</b><br />Singapore or Albert Park. I've had nice memories and those tracks are awesome to drive on.<br /><br /><b>Q: Force India, Virgin Racing, HRT and Scuderia Toro Rosso are just some of the teams that have departed the AtomicF1 championship. Which former team would you most liked to have raced with and why?</b><br />Virgin Racing. I've had some great memories when I was driving with them last season. It was a shame the team didn't get the founding and motivation to race in their last season before I moved over to Williams.<br /><br /><b>Q: You have to design a new F1 circuit, combining all your favourite corners from other tracks around the world. Which three corners are top of your list and why?</b><br />Eau Rouge at Spa, Massenet in Monaco and Epingle at Canada. All challenging corners that I love racing on.<br /><br /><b>Q: What current Formula One regulation would you most like to change and why?</b><br />Corner cutting if you fly off the track. I was slapped with too many drive-throughs this year!<br /><br /><b>Q: If you were a team boss, which current driver would you pick first for your team?</b><br />TurrbalTerror. He is quick and experienced. I wouldn't call him complete yet but he's getting there.<br /><br /><b>Q: You are given the chance to drive any legendary Formula One car of the past (excluding those made by your own team). Which car would you choose?</b><br />McLaren MP4-4. That thing dominated the sport and perhaps kickstarted the majority of the AtomicF1 dream.<br /><br /><b>Q:If you can add one thing to your car, what would it be?</b><br />A better ECU. It's giving me the shits. Plus, I'm guessing Ghost has been pissing in it so I'll fit a toilet for him.<br /><br /><b>Q:Which two drivers would be the Tom and Jerry of AtomicF1?</b><br />There is a Tom and Jerry racing?</p>]]></content>
