              <thumbnail>1717</thumbnail>
              <teaser><![CDATA[In this second installment Lambo answers some more snippets of Trivia from the annals of atomicf1.  Trivial and at the same time giving good insight into the who's who of atomic f1.]]></teaser>
              <content><![CDATA[<p><strong>Q: Only 6 drivers combined have won all the races in the Atomic F1 Championship. How many manufacturers have won races?</strong><br /><b>A:</b> Ironically the answer to this question is also 6. In order of success the McLaren's currently hold the record with 20 wins, Force India a close second with 17 victories. GFI are only one win behind that with 16 victories, followed by Lotus with 5, Renault with 3 and Ferrari with 2 wins.<br /><br /><strong>Q: Ferrari's Flouncy has won a record 22 race victories with Force India, McLaren, GFI and Ferrari. Is this a record for a driver?</strong><br /><b>A:</b> It certainly is. Ferrari's Flouncy has won races driving for 4 separate manufacturers. Second place is Lambo who won his 17 races with either Force India or Renault. Of the remaining race winners, bobaj0r and TurrbalTerror all won their races driving for McLaren, while Ghost and Mark84 won theirs for Lotus and Williams respectively.<br /><br /><strong>Q: Who has won the most GPs in a single season without becoming world champion?</strong><br /><b>A:</b> This one's pretty straight forward. In easily the closest finish seen to date, season 3 came down to the last race in Abu Dhabi between the Lotus of Ghost and the McLaren of Flouncy. With only a handful of points separating them Flouncy would take the title securing his 8th win of the season. The same number as Ghost who would finish second in the proceedings due to his other points finishes.<br /><br /><strong>Q: Which drivers have finished second and third the most often in F1 races won by Flouncy?</strong><br /><b>A:</b> Of Flouncys 22 race victories, the clear leader in this department is Ghost who has finished on the podium below Flouncy on no less than 12 occasions. Second however is Lambo who has done the same in 10 races. Third place surprisingly belongs to Eradicator who's stood on the podium with flouncy 8 times while the rest are rounded out with TurrbalTerror with 6, and one a piece to Sora, ET ROM au and Modz.<br /><br /><strong>Q: How often has the podium in an Atomic F1 race been made up of Flouncy, Lambo and Ghost?</strong><br /><b>A:</b> I had to recheck this fact twice as the result was remarkable. Any combination of Flouncy, Lambo or Ghost standing on the podium in an Atomic F1 championship race has occurred on no less then 19 occasions. It happened just the once in season one, but an amazing 10 times in seasons 2 (including a remarkable run of 4 straight races between round 11 and 14), and 8 times in season 3. It's yet to happen in Season 4 however.</p>]]></content>
